My Idea of Fun is the second novel by Will Self , and was published in 1993 .
Christopher Unborn ( Spanish : Cristóbal Nonato ) is the tenth novel by the Mexican author Carlos Fuentes .
Longest Day is an original novel by Michael Collier .
Palazzi di Genova is a 1622 book written and illustrated by Peter Paul Rubens , depicting and describing the palaces of Genoa , Italy in 72 plates .
The Council of Wyrms boxed set was designed by Bill Slavicsek , and published by TSR , Inc. In 1999 the setting was slightly revised and reprinted as a hardcover book .
`` A Positive '' is a 1998 horror short story by Kaaron Warren .
The Bolshevik Myth ( Diary 1920 - -1922 ) is a book by Alexander Berkman describing his experiences in Bolshevist Russia from 1920 to 1922 , where he saw the aftermath of the Russian Revolution of 1917 .
Fall Out Toy Works is an American comic book limited series , created by Pete Wentz of Fall Out Boy , Darren Romanelli , and Nathan Cabrera .
A Midsummer Tempest is an 1974 alternative history fantasy novel by Poul Anderson .
A Conversation is a play by Australian author David Williamson .
The Conscience of a Conservative is a 1960 book published under the name of Arizona Senator and 1964 Republican presidential candidate Barry Goldwater .
The Underland Chronicles is a critically acclaimed series of five epic fantasy novels by Suzanne Collins , first published between 2003 and 2007 .
De Bello Hispaniensi ( also Bellum Hispaniense ; On the Hispanic War ) is a Latin work continuing Julius Caesar 's commentaries , De Bello Gallico and De Bello Civili , and its sequels by two different unknown authors De Bello Alexandrino and De Bello Africo .
A Dangerous Path is a children 's fantasy novel , the fifth book in the Warriors series , written by Cherith Baldry and Kate Cary under the pseudonym of Erin Hunter .
The Kiss of the Octopus is the twenty - second novel of Patrick Grainville published in éditions du Seuil in 2010 .
Renegade of Kregen is a science fiction novel written by Kenneth Bulmer under the pseudonym of Alan Burt Akers , and is volume thirteen in his extensive Dray Prescot series of sword and planet novels , set on the fictional world of Kregen , a planet of the Antares star system in the constellation of Scorpio .
The Stratagem and other Stories is a small book of short stories written by Aleister Crowley ( 1875 - -1947 ) , occult magician , poet and self - proclaimed prophet of a new Æon .
The Case of Wagner ( German : Der Fall Wagner ) is a book by the philosopher Friedrich Nietzsche , originally published in 1888 .
The John Riddell Murder Case is a novel written by Corey Ford under the pseudonym of John Riddell .
Killing Yourself to Live : 85 % of a True Story is a work of non - fiction written by Chuck Klosterman , first published by Scribner in 2005 .
Opus 200 is Isaac Asimov 's joint two - hundredth book , along with his autobiography In Memory Yet Green ( both books were published on the same day , following his 199th book ) .
The Legion of Space is a science - fiction novel by the American writer Jack Williamson .
Homeroom Diaries is a realistic fiction novel by James Patterson aimed at teenagers .
Midnight Whispers is the fourth novel in the Cutler series , written in 1992 by the ghost - writer of V. C. Andrews novels , Andrew Neiderman .
The True Story of Ah Q is an episodic novella written by Lu Xun , first published as a serial between December 4 , 1921 and February 12 , 1922 .
Now , Now , Markus or , I Need a Bird is a children 's novel by Austrian author Martin Auer , first published in 1988 in German as Bimbo und sein Vogel .
Half a Lifelong Romance ( 半生緣 ) is a Chinese novel by Eileen Chang .
Dolores Claiborne is a 1992 psychological thriller novel by Stephen King .
`` A Short Guide to the City '' is a 1990 short story by American horror writer Peter Straub collected in Houses Without Doors .
Other Losses is a 1989 book by Canadian writer James Bacque , in which Bacque alleges that U.S. General Dwight Eisenhower intentionally caused the deaths by starvation or exposure of around a million German prisoners of war held in Western internment camps briefly after the Second World War .
Number the Stars ( 1989 ) is a work of historical fiction by American author Lois Lowry , about the escape of a Jewish family from Copenhagen during World War II . The story centers on ten - year - old Annemarie Johansen , who lives with her family in Copenhagen in 1943 .
The Misfortunes of Elphin is a novella by Thomas Love Peacock , his fifth long work of fiction , published in 1829 .
`` A Cabin on the Coast '' is a science fiction / fantasy short story by Gene Wolfe , initially published in the February 1984 issue of The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction and collected in Endangered Species ( 1989 ) and The Best Of Gene Wolfe ( 2009 ) .
The Watsons is an unfinished novel by Jane Austen .
`` By His Bootstraps '' is a science fiction novella by Robert A. Heinlein that plays with some of the inherent paradoxes that would be caused by time travel .
Goodbye California is a novel by Scottish author Alistair MacLean , first published in 1977 .
M Is for Magic is a collection of child - friendly short fiction by Neil Gaiman .
The Great Mirror of Male Love ( 男色大鑑 Nanshoku Ōkagami ) , with the subtitle The Custom of Boy Love in Our Land ( 本朝若風俗 Honchō Waka Fūzoku ) is a collection of homosexuality stories by Ihara Saikaku , published in 1687 .
The 1984 autobiography by Julian Lloyd Webber , Travels with My Cello , covers his childhood through to travelling the world as a concert performer in the early 1980s .
The Lives of Flemish , German , and Dutch painters refers to a compilation of artist biographies by Jean - Baptiste Descamps published in the mid 18th - century that were accompanied by illustrations by Charles Eisen .
Vi är inte ensamma - en samling berättelser om våra osynliga hjälpare ( Swedish ) is a 1990 Swedish book about the occult , written by Norwegian - Swedish author Margit Sandemo .
Monsieur Pain is a short novel by Chilean author Roberto Bolaño ( 1953 - -2003 ) .
Praisesong for the Widow is a 1983 novel by Paule Marshall that takes place in the mid-1970s , chronicling the life of Avey Johnson , a 64-year - old African - American widow on a physical and emotional journey in the Caribbean island of Carriacou .
Disney purchased the film rights to the Matched trilogy on September 16 , 2010 , Ally Condie 's birthday , before the book had been released .
Faceless Killers ( Swedish : Mördare utan ansikte ) is a 1991 crime novel by the Swedish writer Henning Mankell , and the first in his acclaimed Wallander series .
Baruničina ljubav ( pronounced ( baruniʧina ʎubaʋ ) ) ( lit . `` Baroness '' love '' ) is a novel written by Croatian writer Ante Kovačić .
L'Aiglon is a play in six acts by Edmond Rostand based on the life of Napoleon II , who was the son of Emperor Napoleon I and his second wife , Empress Marie Louise .
Don Parties On , a play by David Williamson , premiered in Melbourne on January 8 , 2011 .
The Alleluia Files is a science fiction / fantasy novel by Sharon Shinn , published in 1999 .
Church Dogmatics ( German : Kirchliche Dogmatik ) is the fourteen - volume magnum opus of Swiss Protestant theologian Karl Barth , which was published in stages from 1932 to 1967 .
A Couple of Boys Have the Best Week Ever is children 's book written and illustrated by Marla Frazee and set in Malibu , CA .
Shakespeare Wrote for Money is a 2008 collection of English author Nick Hornby 's `` Stuff I 've Been Reading '' columns for The Believer .
Lady into Fox was David Garnett 's first novel under his own name , published in 1922 .
The Liberation Trilogy is a series of military history books about the United States ' involvement in World War II , written by American author Rick Atkinson and published by Henry Holt & Co. The first volume , An Army at Dawn , won the 2003 Pulitzer Prize for History and was a New York Times best seller .
Nightflyers is the title of a 1980 novella by George R. R. Martin , a 1985 short story collection by the same author that includes the novella , and a 1987 science fiction - horror film based on that novella .
The Day of the Pelican is a children 's novel by Katherine Paterson , first published by Clarion Books on October 19 , 2009 .
The Chinese Agent ( 1970 ) is a comic novel by Michael Moorcock .
The Idiot ( Russian : Идио́т , Idiot ) is a novel by the 19th - century Russian author Fyodor Dostoyevsky .
Patsy of Paradise Place , is a romantic fiction novel written by the English author Rosie Harris .
The Shadow over Innsmouth is a horror novella by H. P. Lovecraft , written in November--
Freddy and Fredericka is a satiric novel by Mark Helprin .
A single - volume concise edition , The Popular Handbook of British Birds was produced by Philip Hollom in 1952 .
First published in 1972 ( ISBN 0 - 380 - 01694-X ) , it includes all the short stories about Lord Peter written by Dorothy L. Sayers , most of which were published elsewhere soon after they were written , and some related writings .
`` The Three Hermits '' ( Russian : Три Старца ) is a short story by Russian author Leo Tolstoy ( Lev Nikolayevich Tolstoy ) written in 1885 and first published in 1886 in the weekly periodical Niva ( нива ) .
Argument About Basia ( Polish : Awantura o Basię ) is a Polish novel by Kornel Makuszyński , written in 1936 , but released one year later .
Anandi Gopal is a play written by Ram G. Joglekar ( 1924 - 2004 ) , based on the novel Anandi Gopal by Shrikrishna Janardan Joshi , on the life of Anandi Gopal Joshi .
Little Eyolf ( Lille Eyolf in the original Norwegian title ) is an 1894 play by Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen .
Amazon Adventure is a 1949 children 's novel by the Canadian - born American author Willard Price featuring his `` Adventure '' series characters , Hal and Roger Hunt .
The Silver Wolf is a novel by Alice Borchardt and published by Del Rey Books in 1993 .
Yaqui Delgado Wants to Kick Your Ass is a 2013 award - winning young adult book by Cuban - American author Meg Medina .
Cue for Treason ( 1940 ) is a children 's historical novel written by Geoffrey Trease , and is his best - known work .
The Mice Templar is an American comic book series created by Bryan J. L. Glass , and Michael Avon Oeming that is published by Image Comics .
Border , Breed nor Birth is a science - fiction novella by Dallas McCord `` Mack '' Reynolds .
The Archaeology of Death and Burial is an archaeological study by the English archaeologist Mike Parker Pearson , then a professor at the University of Sheffield .
A Stranger Came Ashore is a 1975 young adult novel written by Scottish author Mollie Hunter .
Nymphomation is a novel by British author Jeff Noon , first published in 1997 .
`` The Dream of Debs '' is a short story by American writer Jack London , first published in the International Socialist Review in January 1909 .
Daughters of the Moon is a novel series by Lynne Ewing .
Miss Betty is a romance novel by Bram Stoker , written in 1898 .
Om fjorten dage ( lit . In Fourteen Days ) is a 1983 short story collection by Danish author Peter Seeberg .
`` The Martian Way '' is a science fiction novella by Isaac Asimov .
Under Kilimanjaro is a non - fiction novel by Ernest Hemingway ( July 21 , 1899 -- July 2 , 1961 ) , edited and published posthumously by Robert W. Lewis and Robert E. Fleming .
The Romance of Leonardo da Vinci ( Russian : Воскресшие боги. Леонардо да Винчи , Resurrected Gods . Leonardo da Vinci , in literal translation ) is the second novel by Dmitry Merezhkovsky , first published in 1900 by Mir Bozhy magazine , then released as a separate edition 1901 .
A Darkling Plain is the fourth and final novel in the Mortal Engines Quartet series written by author Philip Reeve .
Extra(ordinary ) People is a 1984 collection of feminist science fiction stories by Joanna Russ .
Miss Rumphius is a picture book for children written and illustrated by Barbara Cooney and first published by Viking Books in 1982 .
Juoksuhaudantie is a 2004 novel by Finnish author Kari Hotakainen .
Skippy Dies is a 2010 tragicomic novel by Paul Murray .
The Language of the Genes ( HarperCollins , ISBN 0 - 00 - 255020 - 2 ) is a popular science book by Steve Jones about genetics and evolution .
`` The Minority Report '' is a 1956 science fiction short story by Philip K. Dick , first published in Fantastic Universe .
Summer Crossing is Truman Capote 's first novel , written during the 1940s .
To Fear a Painted Devil is a novel by British writer Ruth Rendell .
On the False Embassy ( Ancient Greek : Περὶ τῆς παραπρεσβείας ) is the name of two famous judicial orations , both delivered in 343 BC by the prominent Athenian statesmen and fierce opponents , Demosthenes and Aeschines .
More Die of Heartbreak is a 1987 novel by the American author Saul Bellow , and was his tenth novel .
The Iron Woman is the 1993 sequel to the popular Ted Hughes novel The Iron Man .
Captain Gault is a fictional sea captain created by English writer William Hope Hodgson .
The Emperor 's Snuff - Box is a non - series mystery novel ( 1942 ) by mystery novelist John Dickson Carr .
Le Jour où Beaumont fit connaissance avec sa douleur is a novella written in French by French Nobel laureate writer J. M. G. Le Clézio .
The Templar Salvation is a 2010 novel by Raymond Khoury , and sequel to his debut work The Last Templar .
The Four - Headed Dragon is the 69th title of the Hardy Boys series , written by Franklin W. Dixon .
The Bafut Beagles by British naturalist Gerald Durrell tells the story of Durrell 's collecting expedition to the Cameroons , made in 1949 , with Kenneth Smith .
Sonnet 131 is a sonnet written by William Shakespeare and was first published in a 1609 quarto edition titled Shakespeare 's sonnets .
The Hunger Angel ( German : Atemschaukel ; 2009 ) is a 304-page prose poem by Herta Müller .
Good - bye , My Lady is a novel by James H. Street about a boy and his dog .
De Medicina is a 1st - century medical treatise by Aulus Cornelius Celsus , a Roman encyclopedist and possibly ( but not likely ) a practicing physician .
Royal Exile is the first novel in the Valisar trilogy , by Australian fantasy author Fiona McIntosh .
The Homeward Bounders is a fantasy novel by Diana Wynne Jones with the chilling premise that there is a vast series of parallel universes , all of which serve as the game - boards for a race of demons that delight in war - games and fantasy - games .
Executive Order 11063 was signed by President John F. Kennedy on November 20 , 1962 .
Livets ax ( lit . Ear of Life ) is a 1991 novel by Swedish author Sven Delblanc .
Peace Breaks Out ( 1981 ) is a novel by American author John Knowles , better known for A Separate Peace ( 1959 ) .
Tatja Grimm 's World is a 1987 science fiction novel by American author Vernor Vinge .
In the 1970s Peake 's widow , Maeve Gilmore , wrote a version of Titus Awakes to which she gave the title Search Without End .
Family Under the Bridge is a seasonal young adult novel written by Natalie Savage Carlson about a Parisian named Armand who befriends some children and has adventures in Paris during the Christmas season .
Patriot Reign is a best - selling book by Boston Globe / New York Times sports writer Michael Holley resulting from two years he was given unprecedented access to the inner sanctums of the world champion New England Patriots football operations , as they worked to turn a season of good luck into a legitimate contender of a team .
Echoes in the Darkness is the title of a 1987 book by crime writer Joseph Wambaugh which also became a made - for - TV movie the same year .
Eating the Dinosaur is the sixth book written by Chuck Klosterman , first published by Scribner in 2009 .
L'Oblat ( The Oblate ) is the last novel by the French writer Joris - Karl Huysmans , first published in 1903 .
The Finkler Question is a 2010 novel written by British author Howard Jacobson .
The Different Forms of Flowers on Plants of the Same Species is a book by Charles Darwin first published in 1877 .
Whompyjawed is the debut novel by American author Mitch Cullin .
Tales of a Long Night ( German : Hamlet oder Die lange Nacht nimmt ein Ende ) ( 1956 ) is the last novel of German author Alfred Döblin .
The Prague Orgy ( 1985 ) is a novella by Philip Roth .
Something Happened is Joseph Heller 's second novel ( published in 1974 , thirteen years after Catch-22 ) .
An Englishwoman 's Love - letters is a 1900 novel by Laurence Housman , initially published anonymously .
The Odyssey ( /ˈɒdəsi/ ; Greek : Ὀδύσσεια Odýsseia , pronounced ( o.dýs.sej.ja ) in Classical Attic ) is one of two major ancient Greek epic poems attributed to Homer .
The Chymical Wedding is a 1989 novel by Lindsay Clarke about the intertwined lives of six people in two different eras .
The Lay of Aotrou and Itroun is a poem of 508 lines , written by J. R. R. Tolkien in 1930 and published in Welsh Review in December , 1945 .
Independent People ( Icelandic : Sjálfstætt fólk ) is an epic novel by Nobel laureate Halldór Laxness , originally published in two volumes in 1934 and 1935 ; literally the title means `` Self - standing ( i.e. self - reliant ) folk '' .
Two Fates ( Dve Sudby ) is a poem by Apollon Maykov , first published in 1845 in Saint Petersburg , as a separate edition , under the title `` Two Fates .
Dreams and Fancies is a collection of letters and fantasy , horror and science fiction short stories by American author H. P. Lovecraft .
The Black Cherry Bombshells is a webcomic from DC imprint Zuda Comics , created by Johnny Zito and Tony Trov , illustrated by Sacha Borisich and colors by John Dallaire .
False Mirrors ( Russian : Фальшивые зеркала ) is the second novel in the Labyrinth trilogy of cyberpunk novels written by Russian science fiction writer Sergey Lukyanenko .
`` The Little Black Bag '' is a short story by science fiction author Cyril M. Kornbluth , first published in the July 1950 edition of Astounding Science Fiction .
Let Us Now Praise Famous Men is a book with text by American writer James Agee and photographs by American photographer Walker Evans , first published in 1941 in the United States .
Pedagogy of the Oppressed ( Portuguese : Pedagogia do Oprimido ) , written by educator Paulo Freire , proposes a pedagogy with a new relationship between teacher , student , and society .
The Mockery Bird is a humorous novel by Gerald Durrell , published in 1981 by William Collins , Sons and Co Ltd. The book , like the other works of the author , contains a strong environmental message .
Diego et Frida is a biography of Mexican painters Diego Rivera and Frida Kahlo by French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio .
The Curious Room ( ISBN 0 - 09 - 958621 - 5 ) is a book collecting various plays and scripts by Angela Carter .
Green Grass , Running Water is a 1993 novel by Thomas King , a writer of Cherokee and Greek / German - American descent , and United States and Canadian dual citizenship .
In Watermelon Sugar is a novel written by Richard Brautigan and published in 1968 .
Ripley Bogle is the debut novel of Northern Irish author Robert McLiam Wilson , published in 1989 in the UK although not until 1998 in the US .
The Twelfth Card is the sixth Lincoln Rhyme mystery novel by Jeffery Deaver .
Beasts and Super - Beasts is a collection of short stories , written by Saki ( the literary pseudonym of Hector Hugh Munro ) and first published in 1914 .
The Effects of Cross and Self Fertilisation in the Vegetable Kingdom is a book on evolution in plants by Charles Darwin , first published in 1876 .
The Killer Angels ( 1974 ) is a historical novel by Michael Shaara that was awarded the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction in 1975 .
Falconer 's Lure is a 1957 falconry - based novel by Antonia Forest .
The Partner ( 1997 ) is a legal / thriller novel by noted American author John Grisham .
Deeply Odd ( 2013 ) is the sixth thriller novel in the Odd Thomas series by American writer Dean Koontz .
The Satanic Bible is a collection of essays , observations , and rituals published by Anton LaVey in 1969 .
The Map and the Territory ( French : La carte et le territoire , French pronunciation : ​(la kaʁt e lə tɛʁitwaʁ ) ) is a novel by French author Michel Houellebecq .
Titus Awakes is the editorial title applied to a novel being planned by Mervyn Peake at the time he became too ill to write , about 1960 .
House of Odd is the third graphic novel featuring Dean Koontz 's character Odd Thomas .
Sentenced to Prism ( 1985 ) is a science fiction novel written by Alan Dean Foster , and is a stand - alone entry in his Humanx Commonwealth series of books .
The Fatwa on Terrorism and Suicide Bombings is a 600-page ( Urdu version ) , 512-page ( English version ) Islamic decree by scholar Muhammad Tahir - ul - Qadri which demonstrates from the Quran and Sunnah that terrorism and suicide bombings are unjust and evil , and thus un - Islamic .
The Book of Faith ( Arabic : Kitab al Iman , كتاب الإيمان ) is a book on the Islamic articles of faith written by the 13th century Sunni Islamic scholar Ibn Taymiyyah .
The Moon Is a Harsh Mistress is a 1966 science fiction novel by American writer Robert A. Heinlein , about a Lunar colony 's revolt against rule from Earth .
Barefoot in the Park is a romantic comedy by Neil Simon .
Nordlands Trompet is a tributary poem by Norwegian priest and poet Petter Dass , praising the nature and people of Nordland .
The Metabarons series was written by creator Alejandro Jodorowsky and illustrated by Argentinian artist Juan Giménez .
`` Winter Dreams '' is a short story by F. Scott Fitzgerald that first appeared in Metropolitan Magazine in December 1922 , and was collected in All the Sad Young Men in 1926 .
Kir Ianulea or Kyr Ianulea ( Romanian pronunciation : ( kir jaˈnule̯a ) ) is a fantasy and historical fiction novella or short story , published by Romanian author Ion Luca Caragiale in 1909 .
The Empress 's Tomb ( 2007 ) is a young adult novel by Kirsten Miller , the second in the Kiki Strike series .
Venmurasu ( Tamil : வெண்முரசு ) is a Tamil novel by writer Jeyamohan .
That Printer of Udell 's is a 1903 work of fiction by Harold Bell Wright .
Fox Tales is a 1976 anthology of 16 animal - centered fairy tales from around the world that have been collected and retold by Ruth Manning - Sanders .
Red Indian Folk and Fairy Tales is a 1960 anthology of 19 fairy tales from North American Indian culture that have been collected and retold by Ruth Manning - Sanders .
For Anatole 's Tomb ( French : Pour un tombeau d'Anatole ) is an unfinished poem by the French writer Stéphane Mallarmé .
The Unifying Force is the nineteenth and final installment of the New Jedi Order series of books in the fictional Star Wars expanded universe written by James Luceno .
The Straight Mind and Other Essays is a ( 1992 ) collection of essays by Monique Wittig .
The Concubine 's Secret , as known as The Girl from Junchow in USA , is a 2009 novel by Kate Furnivall ; it is the sequel to The Russian Concubine .
The Lady of Lyons ; or , Love and Pride , commonly known as The Lady of Lyons , is a five act romantic melodrama written in 1838 by Edward Bulwer - Lytton , 1st Baron Lytton .
Thud ! is Terry Pratchett 's 34th Discworld novel , released in the United States of America on September 13 , 2005 , the United Kingdom on 1 October 2005 .
Anna and the French Kiss is the 2010 debut novel of Stephanie Perkins .
The Winner Stands Alone is a novel by Paulo Coelho first published in 2008 .
Heauton Timorumenos ( The Self - Tormentor ) is a play written by Publius Terentius Afer , known in English as `` Terence '' , a dramatist of the Roman Republic .

Chinese Cinderella and the Secret Dragon Society is a historical novel by Adeline Yen Mah , published in 2004 .

So Long a Letter ( translated from Une si longue lettre ) is a semi - autobiographical epistolary novel originally written in French by the Senegalese writer Mariama Bâ .
The Genie of Sutton Place is a 1973 supernatural young adult novel by George Selden , who was most famous for The Cricket in Times Square .
Tris 's Book , a fantasy novel by Tamora Pierce , tells the story of four young mages as they battle pirates and become closer than ever .
Children of Their City ( Swedish : Barn av sin stad ) is a 1962 novel by Swedish author Per Anders Fogelström .

The Judas Boy is Volume V of the novel sequence Alms for Oblivion by Simon Raven , published in 1968 .
Masud Rana is a fictional character created in 1966 by writer Qazi Anwar Hussain , who featured him in over 400 novels .
The Third Twin is a techno - thriller by the British writer Ken Follett and published by Random House publications in 1996 .
Milton Friedman 's book Essays in Positive Economics ( 1953 ) is a collection of earlier articles by the author with as its lead an original essay `` The Methodology of Positive Economics , '' on which this article focuses .
Lord Weary 's Castle , Robert Lowell 's second book of poetry , won the Pulitzer Prize for Poetry in 1947 when Lowell was only thirty .
The Wolf Leader is an English translation by Alfred Allinson of Le Meneur de loups , an 1857 fantasy novel by Alexandre Dumas .
The Bones of Zora is a science fiction novel written by L. Sprague de Camp and Catherine Crook de Camp , the ninth book of the former 's Viagens Interplanetarias series and the seventh of its subseries of stories set on the fictional planet Krishna .
Company K is a 1933 novel by William March , first serialised in parts in the New York magazine The Forum from 1930 to 1932 , and published in its entirety by Smith and Haas on 19 January 1933 , in New York .
Enna Burning is a fantasy novel by Shannon Hale , and the second book in the Books of Bayern series .

The Litigators is a 2011 legal thriller novel by John Grisham , his 25th fiction novel overall .
Mommywood is a 2009 book by Tori Spelling , released on April 14 , 2009 .
In his 2007 book On Nuclear Terrorism , author Michael A. Levi surveys the issue of nuclear terrorism and explores the decisions a terrorist leader might take in pursuing a nuclear plot .
Marigolds in August is a play by South Africa 's Athol Fugard .
`` The Lost Special '' is a short story by Arthur Conan Doyle first published as part of the Round the Fire series in The Strand Magazine of August 1898 .

Beyond the City ( 1892 ) is a novel by the Scottish author Sir Arthur Conan Doyle .
Data Smog is a 1997 book by journalist David Shenk and published by Harper Collins .
The Magic Mountain ( German : Der Zauberberg ) is a novel by Thomas Mann , first published in November 1924 .
The Faraway Tree is a series of popular novels for children by British author Enid Blyton .
Frankensteins of Fraud is a book written by Joseph T. Wells , founder of the Association of Certified Fraud Examiners .
The Songs of Distant Earth is a 1986 science fiction novel by Arthur C. Clarke based upon his 1958 short story of the same title .
Dance of the Happy Shades ( ISBN 0 - 099 - 27377 - 2 ) is a book of short stories by Alice Munro , published by Ryerson Press in 1968 .
Acorna 's Quest ( 1998 ) is a fantasy or science fiction novel by Anne McCaffrey and Margaret Ball .
Wideacre is a 1987 historical novel by Philippa Gregory .
This Boy 's Life is a memoir by American author Tobias Wolff first published in 1989 .
`` The Walrus and the Carpenter '' is a narrative poem by Lewis Carroll that appeared in his book Through the Looking - Glass , published in December 1871 .
The Man with the Getaway Face ( 1963 ) is a crime thriller novel , written by Donald E. Westlake under the pseudonym Richard Stark .
Unleavened Bread is a 1900 novel by American writer Robert Grant , and one of the best selling books of that year .
`` A Mother '' is a short story by James Joyce published in his 1914 collection Dubliners .
The Tigers of Mompracem ( original title : Le Tigri di Mompracem ) is an exotic adventure novel written by Italian author Emilio Salgari , published in 1900 .
In Search of a Concrete Music ( French : À la recherche d'une musique concrète ) , written and published in 1952 , is a French language publication which forms a major part of the experimental composer and theoretician Pierre Schaeffer 's collection of works written to record his own undertakings on the development of musique concrète .
The Year of Billy Miller , a 2014 children 's book written by Kevin Henkes , was a Newbery Honor book in 2014 .
Teseida ( full title : Teseida delle Nozze d’Emilia , or The Theseid , Concerning the Nuptials of Emily ) is a long epic poem written by Giovanni Boccaccio c.1340 - -41 .
Dynasty of Death was the debut novel of the Anglo - American writer Taylor Caldwell ( 1900 - -1985 ) .
The Second Summer of the Sisterhood is a novel written in 2003 by author Ann Brashares .
The Galactic Center Saga is a series of books by author Gregory Benford detailing a galactic war between mechanical and biological life .
The Algiers Motel Incident is a 1968 true crime book by John Hersey .
The Anti - Capitalistic Mentality is a book written by Austrian School economist and libertarian thinker Ludwig von Mises .
Linguistic Imperialism is a book written by Robert Phillipson , research professor at Copenhagen Business School 's Department of English , published in 1992 by Oxford University Press .
On Horsemanship is the English title usually given to Περὶ ἱππικῆς , peri hippikēs , one of the two treatises on horsemanship by the Athenian historian and soldier Xenophon ( c. 430 -- 354 BC ) .
Piet Fluwijn en Bolleke was a Belgian gag - a - day comic strip series drawn by Marc Sleen from 1944 until 1965 .
The Dark Elf Trilogy is a prequel to the Icewind Dale Trilogy by R. A. Salvatore .
The Courtney Novels are a series of thirteen novels published between 1964 and 2009 by Wilbur Smith .
Where were you last Pluterday ? is a science fiction novel by Paul van Herck , originally released in Dutch in 1968 as Sam , of de Pluterdag by J.M. Meulenhoff ( in their science fiction and fantasy range M = SF as the 14th book of the range ) and released in English by DAW books in 1973 .
Pandemia is a 2006 post - apocalyptic teen novel written by American author Johnathan Rand ( a pseudonym of Christopher Wright ) .
Quasars , Redshifts and Controversies is a 1987 book by Halton Arp , an astronomer famous for his Atlas of Peculiar Galaxies ( 1966 ) .
The Queen of the Damned ( 1988 ) is the third novel of Anne Rice 's The Vampire Chronicles series .
The Return of the Black Widowers is a collection of short mystery stories by Isaac Asimov featuring his fictional club of mystery solvers , the Black Widowers .
The Art of Being Right : 38 Ways to Win an Argument ( Eristische Dialektik : Die Kunst , Recht zu behalten ; 1831 ) is an acidulous and sarcastic treatise written by the German philosopher Arthur Schopenhauer in sarcastic deadpan .
Hadrian the Seventh ( also known as `` Hadrian VII '' ) is a 1904 novel by the English novelist Frederick Rolfe , who wrote under the pseudonym `` Baron Corvo '' .
The Life and Work of Sigmund Freud is a biography of Sigmund Freud by Ernest Jones .
The Invasion of 1910 is a 1906 novel written mainly by William Le Queux ( along with H. W. Wilson providing the naval chapters ) .
Yonie Wondernose is a 1944 picture book by Marguerite de Angeli , who would later win the Newbery Medal for The Door in the Wall .
The Fifth Son of the Shoemaker is a book by Donald Corley , illustrated by the author .
Nebula Maker is a science fiction novel by Olaf Stapledon , published posthumously by Bran 's Head Books in 1976 .
I 'll Be The Devil is a play by Leo Butler that was commissioned by the Royal Shakespeare Company and written in response to The Tempest by William Shakespeare .
XPD is a spy novel by Len Deighton , published in 1981 , and set in 1979 , roughly contemporaneous with the time it was written .
The Outlaw 's Silver is the title of a Hardy Boys Digest novel , written by Franklin W. Dixon .
The Coelbren y Beirdd ( English : `` Bards ' alphabet '' ) is a runic alphabet system created in the late eighteenth century by the literary forger Edward Williams , best known as Iolo Morganwg .
Chinese Shadows is a book written by Simon Leys , which is the pseudonym for Belgian Sinologist Pierre Ryckmans .
The Wanting Seed is a dystopian novel by the English author Anthony Burgess , written in 1962 .
While I Was Gone is the 1999 novel by Sue Miller , and was chosen as an Oprah 's Book Club selection in May 2000 .
Sister of the Bride is a 1963 young adult novel by Beverly Cleary .
The Fuller Memorandum is the third novel by Charles Stross in his `` Laundry '' series of Lovecraftian spy thrillers .
Agatha Raisin and the Deadly Dance is the fifteenth Agatha Raisin mystery novel by Marion Chesney under her pseudonym M. C. Beaton .
The Mist is a horror novella by the American author Stephen King , in which the small town of Bridgton , Maine is suddenly enveloped in an unnatural mist that conceals otherworldly monsters .
The Fortified House in Scotland is a five - volume book by the Scottish author Nigel Tranter .
Dilvish , the Damned is a collection of fantasy stories by American writer Roger Zelazny , first published in 1982 .
Intrigue and Love , sometimes Love and Intrigue , Love and Politics or Luise Miller ( German : Kabale und Liebe , literally `` Cabal and Love '' ) is a five - act play , written by the German dramatist Friedrich Schiller ( 1759 - -1805 ) .
Wildsiderz is a comic book series created by J. Scott Campbell and Andy Hartnell , and published by Wildstorm Productions .
The Coldfire Trilogy is a science fiction / fantasy trilogy written by Celia S. Friedman .
Power of Faerûn was written by Ed Greenwood and Eric L. Boyd , and published in March 2006 .
Beggars in Spain is a 1993 science fiction novel by Nancy Kress .
All the Earth , Thrown to the Sky is a young adult fiction novel written by American author Joe R. Lansdale .
Marx the First is a 1973 novel by Scottish writer Bruce Marshall .
Merlin 's Ring is a fantasy novel by H. Warner Munn , the third in a series of three based on Arthurian legend .
All the Wrong Questions is a four - part young adult series and prequel to A Series of Unfortunate Events by Lemony Snicket ( pen name of American author Daniel Handler ) .
Fantastic Four : 1234 is a four - issue comic book limited series featuring the Fantastic Four , written by Grant Morrison and illustrated by Jae Lee and published by Marvel Comics under the Marvel Knights imprint .
The Water - Babies , A Fairy Tale for a Land Baby is a children 's novel by the Reverend Charles Kingsley .
Scorpion Mountain is the fifth instalment in the Brotherband novel series by Australian author John Flanagan .
North of Boston is a 1914 poetry collection by Robert Frost .
Complete Divine was written by David Noonan , and was published in May 2004 .
Seven Days to a Killing is a British spy novel by Clive Egleton , published in 1973 .
Under the Sun of Satan ( French : Sous le soleil de Satan ) was the first novel published by Georges Bernanos .
Ocean Under the Ice is a science fiction novel by Robert L. Forward , collaborating with his wife , Martha Dodson Forward .
The Road of Azrael is a collection of historical short stories by Robert E. Howard .
The Theory of Communicative Action ( German : Theorie des kommunikativen Handelns ) is a 1981 book by Jürgen Habermas , in which he continues his project set out in On the Logic of the Social Sciences of finding a way to ground `` the social sciences in a theory of language . ''
Systematics and the Origin of Species from the Viewpoint of a Zoologist is a book written by zoologist and evolutionary biologist Ernst Mayr that was first published in 1942 by Columbia University Press .
Vampirates is a series of books by British author Justin Somper , about a set of twin children , Connor and Grace Tempest , who get separated at sea and are picked up by two very different ships .
My Lady Ludlow is a novel ( over 77,000 words in the Project Gutenberg text ) by Elizabeth Gaskell .
Maskeblomstfamilien is a novel by the Norwegian author Lars Saabye Christensen .
The History of The Lord of the Rings is a 4-volume work by Christopher Tolkien that documents the process of J. R. R. Tolkien 's writing of The Lord of the Rings .
Bone Quill is the sequel to Hollow Earth from sibling writing pair John Barrowman and Carole Barrowman , published in February 2013 .
Little Nellie 007 ( ISBN 978 - 0 - 907595 - 75 - 5 ) ( 1991 ) is a book by Bruce Barrymore Halpenny about the James Bond autogyro , Little Nellie as featured in the film You Only Live Twice and her `` father '' , Wing Commander Retd .
`` The Evil Clergyman '' is an excerpt from a letter written by American horror fiction writer H. P. Lovecraft in 1933 .
Arms and the Man is a comedy by George Bernard Shaw , whose title comes from the opening words of Virgil 's Aeneid , in Latin :
Pelle Svanslös ( English : Peter - No - Tail ) is a fictional anthropomorphic cat created by the Swedish author Gösta Knutsson and a children 's book series about him .
Fahrenheit 451 is a dystopian novel by Ray Bradbury published in 1953 .
Dona Flor and Her Two Husbands ( Portuguese : Dona Flor e Seus Dois Maridos ) is a Brazilian novel , written by Jorge Amado in 1966 and published in English in 1969 .
Beyond Black is a 2005 novel by English writer Hilary Mantel .
Miss Sara Sampson ( Miß Sara Sampson ) is a play by the Enlightenment philosopher , Gotthold Ephraim Lessing .
The Island of Doctor Death and Other Stories and Other Stories is a short story collection by American science fiction author Gene Wolfe .
Doglands ( 2011 ) is a children 's fantasy novel written by Tim Willocks .
The Costello Memoirs is a collection of writings by Australian politician and long - standing treasurer and deputy Liberal leader Peter Costello and co - authored by former New South Wales Liberal Leader and Costello 's father - in - law , Peter Coleman .
The Case of Charles Dexter Ward is a short novel ( 51,500 words ) by H. P. Lovecraft , written in early 1927 , but not published during the author 's lifetime .
The Chancellor Manuscript is a 1977 novel , by American writer Robert Ludlum , about the `` alleged '' secret files of J. Edgar Hoover and how they disappeared after his death , and how they possibly could be used to force people in high places to do the bidding of those who possessed the secrets contained therein .
Bartholomew and the Oobleck is a 1949 book by Dr. Seuss ( Theodor Geisel ) .
Cradock Nowell : a tale of the New Forest is a three - volume novel by R. D. Blackmore published in 1866 .
Dragonmarked was written by Keith Baker , C.A. Suleiman , and Michelle Lyons , and published in November 2006 .
The Haunted Pampero is a collection of fantasy and other short stories by William Hope Hodgson .
Winston 's War is a 2003 novel by Michael Dobbs that presents a fictional account of the struggle of Winston Churchill to combat the appeasement policies of Prime Minister Neville Chamberlain .
The Phantom Tollbooth is a children 's adventure novel and modern fairy tale by Norton Juster .
Fucking A is a play written by American playwright Suzan - Lori Parks .
News from Nowhere ( 1890 ) is a classic work combining utopian socialism and soft science fiction written by the artist , designer and socialist pioneer William Morris .
The Story of Mr Sommer is a novella by the German writer Patrick Süskind .
Fortunata y Jacinta ( Fortunata and Jacinta ) , was written by Benito Pérez Galdós in 1887 .
A Tangled Tale is a collection of 10 brief humorous stories by Lewis Carroll ( Charles Lutwidge Dodgson ) , published serially between April 1880 and March 1885 in The Monthly Packet magazine .
Letter to My Daughter ( 2009 ) is the third book of essays by African - American writer and poet Maya Angelou .
The Aquariums of Pyongyang , by Kang Chol - hwan and Pierre Rigoulot , is an account of the imprisonment of Kang Chol - Hwan and his family in the Yodok concentration camp in North Korea .
Red as Blood , or Tales from the Sisters Grimmer is a short story collection of dark fantasy retellings of popular fairytales by British author Tanith Lee .
Cerebus (; also Cerebus the Aardvark ) is a comic book series created by Canadian cartoonist Dave Sim , which ran from December 1977 until March 2004 .
Small Moral Works ( Italian : Operette morali ) is a collection of dialogues and fictional essays by italian poet and philosopher Giacomo Leopardi , written between 1824 and 1832 .
Smoky the Cowhorse is a novel by Will James that was the winner of the 1927 Newbery Medal .
The Faithful River was a 1912 novel written in Paris by Polish writer Stefan Żeromski .
The Nonexistent Knight ( Italian : Il cavaliere inesistente ) is an allegorical fantasy novel by Italo Calvino , first published in Italian 1959 and in English translation in 1962 .
Arlequin roi de Serendib is a three - act farce by Alain - René Lesage .
`` Old Man in New World '' is a short story by Olaf Stapledon , published as a separate volume by George Allen and Unwin in 1944 .
Crito ( /ˈkraɪtoʊ/ KRY - toh or /ˈkriːtoʊ/ KREE - toh ; Ancient Greek : Κρίτων ( krítɔːn ) ) is a dialogue by the ancient Greek philosopher Plato .
Thaddeus of Warsaw was an 1803 novel written by Jane Porter .
Genera Plantarum is a publication of Swedish naturalist Carl Linnaeus ( 1701 - -1778 ) .
Genetiks is a French 3 issues comics created by Richard Marazano and Jean - Michel Ponzio .
The Extended Phenotype is a 1982 book by Richard Dawkins in which he introduced a biological concept of the same name .
Luca 's Secret ( Italian : Il Segreto di Luca ) is a 1956 romance novel by Ignazio Silone .
A Pack of Liars is a children fiction novel by Anne Fine .
Stalin 's Ghost is a crime novel by Martin Cruz Smith set in Russia circa 2005 .
Thank You , Fog : last poems by W. H. Auden is a posthumous book of poems by W. H. Auden , published in 1974 .
To Kill a Child ( Swedish : Att döda ett barn ) is a short story by Stig Dagerman .
The Most Beautiful Woman in Town & Other Stories is a collection of anecdotal short stories by American author Charles Bukowski .
A Moveable Feast is a memoir by American author Ernest Hemingway about his years as a struggling , young , expatriate journalist and writer in Paris in the 1920s .
Five on a Treasure Island ( published in 1942 ) is a popular children 's book by Enid Blyton .
Freddy and the Ignormus ( 1941 ) is the 8th book in the humorous children 's series Freddy the Pig by author Walter R. Brooks and illustrator Kurt Wiese .
The Paul Street Boys ( Hungarian : A Pál utcai fiúk ) is a youth novel by the Hungarian writer Ferenc Molnár , first published in 1906 .
The Book of Urizen is one of the major prophetic books of the English writer William Blake , illustrated by Blake 's own plates .
The Pump House Gang is a 1968 collection of essays and journalism by Tom Wolfe .
Five on a Hike Together is the tenth novel in the Famous Five series by Enid Blyton .

The Crusades Through Arab Eyes ( French : Les Croisades vues par les Arabes ) is a French language historical essay by Lebanese author Amin Maalouf .
The Orcs of Thar is an accessory for the Dungeons & Dragons fantasy role - playing game , written by Bruce Heard and published by TSR in 1988 .
The Taking is a 2004 novel written by Dean Koontz .
History of the Iranian Constitutional Revolution ( Persian : تاریخ مشروطهٔ ایران‎‎ ) by the Iranian historian Ahmad Kasravi is the most accurate account of the Persian Constitutional Revolution .
At Any Cost ? is a play by Australian playwright David Williamson .
Ham Hindu Nahin ( Punjabi : ਹਮ ਹਿੰਦੂ ਨਹੀਂ ; Translation : We are not Hindus ) , also spelled as Hum Hindu Nahin , is a 19th - century Punjabi book by Kahn Singh Nabha , on the distinction of the Sikhism and identity .
In June 2011 , Vicky Bullett was inducted into the Women 's Basketball Hall of Fame in Knoxville , Tennessee along with Ruthie Bolton , Muffett McGraw , Val Ackerman , Pearl Moore , and Lometa Odem .
In 2004 , Lia van Leer was awarded the Israel Prize for her lifetime achievement & special contribution to society and the State of Israel .
Ekaterina Kovalevskaya ( Russian : Екатерина Ковалевская ; born 17 April 1974 in Rostov - on - Don ) is a Russian chess player with the FIDE titles of International Master ( IM ) and Woman Grandmaster ( WGM ) .
Henry Miles , FRS ( 2 Jun 1698 -- 10 Feb 1763 ) was an English Dissenting minister and scientific writer ; a Fellow of the Royal Society known for experiments on electricity .
Herrmann Gustav Karl Max von Fabeck ( 6 May 1854 - † 16 December 1916 ) was a Prussian military officer and a German General der Infantarie during World War I. A competent and highly decorated commander , von Fabeck is a recipient of the Pour le Mérite , Prussia 's and Germany 's highest military honor .
Max Stotz ( born 13 February 1912 in Mannswörth , Lower Austria , MIA 19 August 1943 near Vitebsk ) was a German former Luftwaffe flying ace and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
Nino Maisuradze ( Georgian : ნინო მაისურაძე ) , is a Woman Grandmaster chess player and two - time French Women 's Chess Champion .
Edward Alexander Walker ( October 2 , 1864 -- October 24 , 1946 ) was a Sergeant serving in the United States Marine Corps during the Boxer Rebellion who received the Medal of Honor for bravery .
Igor Zugic ( 23 December 1981 ) , is a Canadian International Master of chess who was the 2006 Canadian Champion .
Thomas A. Pope ( December 15 , 1894 -- June 14 , 1989 ) was a soldier in the United States Army who received the Medal of Honor for his actions in the Battle of Hamel during World War I. For this action , he was also awarded the Distinguished Conduct Medal by King George V.
Adolf Ax ( 23 June 1906 , Mouscron -- 6 February 1983 ) was a German SS - Oberführer ( Senior Colonel / Brigadier General ) , who was decorated with Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
Christian Bauer ( born 11 January 1977 in Forbach , Moselle ) is a French chess Grandmaster and author .
Rusudan Goletiani ( Georgian : რუსუდან გოლეთიანი ; born September 8 , 1980 in Sukhumi ) is a Georgian - American chess player who holds the FIDE titles of International Master ( IM ) and Woman Grandmaster ( WGM ) .
John - Paul Wallace ( born 19 November 1976 in Liverpool , New South Wales ) is a professional chess player awarded the title of International Master in 1996 by FIDE ( World Chess Federation ) .
In 1973 , the Pinkas HaKehillot ( Encyclopedia of Jewish Communities ) project of Yad Vashem was awarded the Israel Prize , for its special contribution to society and the State .
In the 2006 New Year Honours List , Ian Bell was appointed Member of the Order of the British Empire for his role in the successful Ashes campaign of 2005 .
Josephine Barstow was made a Dame Commander of the Order of the British Empire in 1995 .
Nikolajs Galdiņš ( 9 October 1902 -- 5 October 1945 ) was an Obersturmbannführer ( lieutenant Colonel ) in the Waffen SS during World War II . He was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .
In 2000 , `` Let 's All Go to the Lobby '' was selected for preservation in the United States National Film Registry by the Library of Congress as being `` culturally , historically , or aesthetically significant '' .
Raymond Leppard was appointed a Commander of the Order of the British Empire ( CBE ) by The Queen .
Nari Ward is the recipient of numerous awards including the American Academy of Arts and Letters ' Willard L. Metcalf Award ( 1998 ) , Pollock Krasner Foundation grant ( 1996 ) , The National Endowment for the Arts ( 1994 ) , and the John Simon Guggenheim Fellowship ( 1992 ) .
James T. Clancy ( 1833 - -December 1870 ) was a Sergeant in the Union Army during the American Civil War who was awarded the Medal of Honor for his actions during the Battle of Vaughan Road .
Len Beadell was awarded the British Empire Medal in 1958 for his work constructing the Gunbarrel Highway .
On 24 May 2007 , the National Constitution Center in Philadelphia announced that Bono would receive the Philadelphia Liberty Medal on 27 September 2007 for his work to end world poverty and hunger .
In 2007 Banco del Libro won the biggest prize in children 's literature , the Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award from the Swedish Arts Council , recognising its `` long - term sustainable work '' as a promoter of reading .
Richard Arthur Samuel Bywater GC , GM ( 3 November 1913 -- 6 April 2005 ) , known as Arthur Bywater , won the George Cross and George Medal , one of only eight people to have been awarded both medals , and the only civilian .
On October 5 , 2002 , Rosalynn Carter was inducted into the National Women 's Hall of Fame in Seneca Falls , New York .
Florent Guillain was appointed Commander of the Legion of Honour .
Ferenc Sánta Jr. ( born March 2 , 1945 ) is a Kossuth Prize and Franz Liszt Prize - winning Hungarian violinist , fiddler and the artistic director of The Hungarian National Gipsy Orchestra .
For The Collected Poems of Howard Nemerov ( 1977 ) , he won the National Book Award for Poetry , Pulitzer Prize for Poetry , and Bollingen Prize .
Walter Kubisch ( 7 September 1918 -- 6 October 1944 ) was a Luftwaffe wireless radio operator of World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
Arnold Hardy ( February 2 , 1922 -- December 5 , 2007 ) was an American amateur photographer who won the 1947 Pulitzer Prize for Photography .
Enid Bibby was made Dame Commander of the Order of the British Empire in the Queen 's Birthday Honours of 2004 .
Mehdi Ali oglu Huseynov , famed under the pseudonym Mehdi Huseyn ( Azerbaijani : Mehdi Hüseyn ) -- was an Azerbaijani and Soviet writer and critic , laureate of the State Stalin Prize of the third degree ( 1950 ) and member of the All - Union Communist Party since 1941 .
Jean Caylar d'Anduze de Saint - Bonnet , Marquis de Toiras ( 1585 - -1636 ) , often just called Toiras , was a Marshal of France of the 17th century .
Salvador J. Lara ( 1920 -- September 1 , 1945 ) was a U.S. Army veteran of World War II and recipient of the Medal of Honor .
John Divane ( VC ) ( Also known as Devine and Duane ) ( November 1823 -- 1 December 1888 ) was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Fritz Gromotka ( 2 June 1915 -- 2 November 1979 ) was a German Luftwaffe ace and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross during World War II . Fritz Gromotka was credited with 29 aerial victories , 27 on the Western Front and 2 on the Eastern Front .
`` Si la vie est cadeau '' ( `` If Life is a Gift '' ) by Jean - Pierre Millers ( music ) and Alain Garcia ( lyrics ) , was the winner of the Eurovision Song Contest 1983 , performed in French by French singer Corinne Hermès for Luxembourg .
Professor Yona Kosashvili MD ( born July 3 , 1970 ) is an Israeli chess Grandmaster and surgeon .
In 2007 , Dance , Girl , Dance was selected for preservation in the United States National Film Registry by the Library of Congress as being `` culturally , historically , or aesthetically significant '' , describing it as Arzner 's `` most intriguing film '' and a `` meditation on the disparity between art and commerce .
Ignatius Joseph Kasimo Hendrowahyono ( 10 April 1900 -- 1 August 1986 ) is a National Hero of Indonesia and Indonesian politician .
Ernest Childers ( February 1 , 1918 -- March 17 , 2005 ) was a United States Army officer and a recipient of the United States military 's highest decoration , the Medal of Honor , for his valorous actions in World War II .
Leroy Hood won the 2011 Fritz J. and Dolores H. Russ Prize `` for automating DNA sequencing that revolutionized biomedicine and forensic science '' and the 2003 Lemelson - MIT Prize for inventing `` four instruments that have unlocked much of the mystery of human biology '' by helping decode the genome .
Evelyn Miot ( born 1943 ) , Miss Haiti Universe , was the first black woman to reach the top fifteen finalists position in the Miss Universe pageant .
On 26 January 2011 , Peter Costello was appointed a Companion of the Order of Australia for `` eminent service to the Parliament of Australia , particularly through the development of landmark economic policy reforms in the areas of taxation , foreign investment , superannuation and corporate regulation , and through representative roles with global financial organisations '' .
Joachim Schepke ( 8 March 1912 -- 17 March 1941 ) was a German U - boat commander during World War II . He was the seventh recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
Ekaterina Atalik ( née Polovnikova ; born 14 November 1982 in Kirov ) is a Russian - Turkish chess player , who holds the titles of International Master and Woman Grandmaster .
Josef Beckmann ( 4 May 1920 -- 6 December 2001 ) was a highly decorated Leutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Aleksandr Zarkhi was granted the honorary title of People 's Artist of the USSR in 1969 and received Stalin Prize in 1946 .
Sandipan Chanda ( born 13 August 1983 ) is a chess Grandmaster hailing from the city of Kolkata ( Calcutta ) in the Indian state of West Bengal .
Hans - Babo von Rohr ( 9 October 1922 , Wolletz -- 14 February 1945 ) was a highly decorated Oberleutnant of the Reserves in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
Hans Götz ( 2 June 1919 -- 4 August 1943 ) was a former German Luftwaffe fighter ace and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross during World War II . Hans Götz was credited with 82 victories in 600 combat missions .
Florin Felecan ( born 7 April 1980 ) is a chess International Master .
Hans Ree ( born 15 September 1944 in Amsterdam ) is a Dutch Grandmaster of chess and is a columnist and chess writer for the NRC Handelsblad .
Jedh Colby Barker ( June 20 , 1945 -- September 21 , 1967 ) was a United States Marine Corps Lance Corporal who posthumously received the Medal of Honor for heroism during the Vietnam War in September 1967 .
Karl Körner ( 19 April 1920 -- 8 August 1997 ) was a Hauptscharführer in the Waffen SS during World War II . He was a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .
Apisamai Srirangsan ( Thai : อภิสมัย ศรีรังสรรค์ ; rtgs : Aphisamai Sirangsan ) , nicknamed Birth ( Thai : เบิร์ท ) ( born December 15 , 1974 in Bangkok , Thailand ) was Miss Thailand 1999 .
Dale Eldon Christensen ( May 31 , 1920- August 4 , 1944 ) was a United States Army officer and a recipient of the United States military 's highest decoration -- the Medal of Honor -- for his actions in World War II .
On September 13 of 1943 , Oleg Koshevoy was posthumously awarded the title of the Hero of the Soviet Union , the Order of Lenin , and later , the Medal `` Partisan of the Patriotic War '' 1st class .
Wulfnoth Cild ( died c. 1014 ) was a South Saxon thegn who is regarded by historians as the probable father of Godwin , Earl of Wessex , and thus the grandfather of King Harold Godwinson .
Kristin Sigurdsdatter ( ca . 1125 - 1178 ) was a Norwegian princess and mother of King Magnus V of Norway .
Ernst - Wilhelm Hoffmann ( 27 September 1904 -- 27 August 1994 ) was a highly decorated Oberst in the Wehrmacht during World War II who was the last commander of the 4 .
James Hobart Ford ( May 22 , 1829 -- January 12 , 1867 ) was a Union general during the American Civil War , notable for his contributions in the Trans - Mississippi Theater of the war .
NGC 3918 is a bright planetary nebula in the constellation Centaurus , that is called the `` Blue Planetary '' or `` The Southerner '' .
W33A is a protostar located approximately 12,000 light - years away from Earth , in the constellation Sagittarius .
HD 5319 is an 8th magnitude star approximately 370 light years away in the constellation Cetus .
33 Arietis ( abbreviated 33 Arietis ) is a binary star in the northern constellation of Aries .
SN 1997D , discovered on January 1997 in galaxy NGC 1536 in Reticulum constellation is a first clearly identified example of atypical Type II supernova with a very low luminosity and expansion velocity .
HD 86081 is a yellow - white dwarf star in the constellation Sextans south of the celestial equator .
PSR B1620 - 26 is a binary star system located at a distance of 3,800 parsecs ( 12,400 light - years ) in the globular cluster of Messier 4 ( M4 , NGC 6121 ) in the constellation of Scorpius .
17 Aquarii ( abbreviated 17 Aqr ) is a spectroscopic binary star in the constellation of Aquarius .
The Owl Nebula ( Messier 97,M97 , NGC 3587 ) is a planetary nebula located approximately 2,030 light years away in the constellation Ursa Major .
Arp 273 is a group of interacting galaxies , lying 300 million light years away in the constellation Andromeda .
NGC 5753 is a spiral galaxy in the constellation Boötes .
3 Boötis ( abbr . : 3 Boo ) is a star in the constellation Boötes .
Simeis 147 , also known as the Spaghetti Nebula , SNR G180.0 - 01.7 or Sharpless 2 - 240 , is a supernova remnant ( SNR ) in the Milky Way , straddling the border between the constellations Auriga and Taurus .
Kepler-5 is a star located in the constellation Cygnus in the field of view of the Kepler Mission , a NASA project aimed at detecting planets in transit of , or passing in front of , their host stars as seen from Earth .
Mu Ophiuchi ( μ Oph ) is a star in the constellation Ophiuchus .
NGC 3718 , also called Arp 214 , is a galaxy located approximately 52 million light years from Earth in the constellation Ursa Major .
6 Boötis or e Boötis is a star in the constellation Boötes .
NGC 1275 ( also known as Perseus A or Caldwell 24 ) is a type 1.5 Seyfert galaxy located around 237 million light - years away in the direction of the constellation Perseus .
HD 30562 is a 6th magnitude F - type main sequence star located approximately 86 light years away in the constellation of Eridanus .
NGC 1261 , also known as Caldwell 87 , is a globular cluster in the constellation Horologium , first discovered by James Dunlop in 1826 .
30 Herculis ( 30 Her ) , or g Herculis , is a star in the constellation Hercules .
NGC 147 ( also known as DDO3 or Caldwell 17 ) is a dwarf spheroidal galaxy about 2.58 Mly away in the constellation Cassiopeia .
Lambda Capricorni ( λ Cap , λ Capricorni ) is a star in the constellation Capricornus .
114 Tauri ( 114 Tau ) is a blue main - sequence star in the constellation Taurus .
IM Pegasi is a variable binary star system approximately 329 light - years away in the constellation of Pegasus .
SN 2008 ha was a type Ia supernova which was first observed around November 7 , 2008 in the galaxy UGC 12682 , which lies in the constellation Pegasus at a distance of about 21.3 megaparsecs ( 69 Mly ) from Earth .
HD 180902 b is an extrasolar planet orbiting the K - type star HD 180902 approximately 359 light years away in the constellation Sagittarius .
NGC 7027 is a very young and dense planetary nebula located around 3,000 light - years ( 920 pc ) away in the constellation Cygnus .
MOA-2007-BLG-192L is a low - mass red dwarf star or brown dwarf , approximately 3,000 light - years away in the constellation of Sagittarius .
V4641 Sagittarii ( V4641 Sgr ) is a variable X - ray binary star system in the constellation Sagittarius .
Psi Scorpii ( ψ Sco , ψ Scorpii ) is a star in the constellation Scorpius .
HD 220466 is a F - type subgiant or main sequence star in the constellation Aquarius .
Mu Horologii ( μ Horologii , μ Hor ) is a yellow - white carbon star of ( visual ) apparent magnitude 5.128 in the constellation Horologium .
LHS 1723 is a nearby red dwarf star of spectral type M4.0 , located in constellation Eridanus at 17.4 light - years from Earth .
HD 140283 , informally nicknamed Methuselah star , is a metal - poor subgiant star about 190 light years away from the Earth in the constellation Libra .
2 Ceti ( 2 Cet ) is a star in the constellation Cetus .
Pi Aquarii ( π Aqr , π Aquarii ) is the Bayer designation for a binary star in the equatorial constellation of Aquarius .
81 Aquarii ( abbreviated 81 Aqr ) is a star in the constellation of Aquarius .
The Eyes Galaxies ( NGC 4435-NGC 4438 , also known as Arp 120 ) are a pair of galaxies about 52 million light - years away in the constellation Virgo .
25 Arietis ( abbreviated 25 Ari ) is a star in the constellation of Cetus .
Psi Tauri ( ψ Tau , ψ Tauri ) is a star in the constellation Taurus .
Gliese 176 b is a super - Earth exoplanet approximately 31 light years away in the constellation of Taurus .
NGC 42 is a galaxy in the Pegasus constellation .
NGC 5189 ( Gum 47 , IC 4274 , nicknamed Spiral Planetary Nebula ) is a planetary nebula in the constellation Musca .
HD 32518 is a 6th magnitude K - type giant star located approximately 390 light years away in the constellation of Camelopardalis .
HD 8574 is a yellow - white star in the constellation Pisces .
L 1159 - 16 is a red dwarf in the northern constellation of Aries .
Delta Eridani ( δ Eri , δ Eridani ) is a 3.54 magnitude star in the constellation of Eridanus .
NGC 3190 is a spiral galaxy with tightly wound arms and lying in the constellation Leo .
NGC 4790 is a Barred Spiral Galaxy ( SBc ) located in the vicinity of the constellation Virgo .
Omicron Lupi ( ο Lup ) is a star in the constellation Lupus .
HR 2096 ' , also known as HD 40325 is a double star in the constellation Auriga .
HD 130458 is a double star in the southern circumpolar constellation of Apus .
Pi Cephei ( π Cep ) is a trinary star located in the constellation Cepheus .
Upsilon Tauri ( υ Tau , υ Tauri ) is a triple star system in the constellation Taurus and a member of the Hyades star cluster .
98 Aquarii ( abbreviated 98 Aqr ) is a star in the equatorial constellation of Aquarius .
R Coronae Australis ( R CrA ) is a variable star in the constellation Corona Australis .
Westerlund 1 ( also called Ara Cluster , designated Wd1 ) is a compact young super star cluster in the Milky Way galaxy , about 3.5 - -5 kpc away from Earth .
NGC 1055 is an edge - on spiral galaxy located in the constellation Cetus that has a prominent nuclear bulge crossed by a wide , knotty , dark lane of dust and gas .
PKS 2000 - 330 ( also known as QSO B2000 - 330 ) is a quasar located in the constellation Sagittarius .
Kepler-32b ( alt . name KOI 952.01 ) is an extrasolar planet in orbit around its M - dwarf - type star in the Kepler-32 system , constellation of Cygnus .
Theta Octantis ( θ Oct ) is an orange giant star in the constellation Octans .
NGC 44 is a binary star system ( both type F4 ) located in the Andromeda constellation .
Alpha Coronae Australis ( α CrA , α Coronae Australis ) is a star in the constellation Corona Australis .
27 Monocerotis ( 27 Mon ) is a star in the constellation Monoceros .
NGC 6604 is an open star cluster located 5500 light years away in the constellation of Serpens and is located about two degrees north of the Eagle Nebula .
Abell 2142 , or A2142 , is a huge , X - ray luminous galaxy cluster in the constellation Corona Borealis .
HD 2942 is a triple star system in the constellation Andromeda located approximately 158 parsecs ( 520 ly ) away .
Pegasus Field ( ICAO : NZPG ) is an airstrip in Antarctica , the southernmost of three airfields serving McMurdo Station .
Yavorov Peak ( Yavorov Vrah \'ya - vo - rov ' vr&h\ ) is an ice - covered peak of elevation 640 m in the Delchev Ridge of the Tangra Mountains on eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .

The Geologists Range is a mountain range about 55 km ( 34 mi ) long , standing between the heads of Lucy and Nimrod Glaciers in Antarctica .

Hood Glacier ( 83 ° 55′S 173 ° 10′E ) is a glacier about 25 nautical miles ( 46 km ) long draining northward from Siege Dome in the Commonwealth Range of Antarctica .
Sartorius Point is a sharp ice - free tipped point formed by an offshoot of Viskyar Ridge and marking the south extremity of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .

Far East prisoners of war is a term used in the United Kingdom to describe former British and Commonwealth prisoners of war held in the Far East during the Second World War .
Vänortsparken ( English : Twin Towns ' Park ) , is a park in central Umeå , Västerbotten County , Sweden .

Social Democracy and Progress ( Catalan : Socialdemocràcia i Progrés , SDP ) is a political party in Andorra led by Víctor Naudi Zamora .
Alaşa ( also , Alasha and Alashakend ) is a village and municipality in the Astara Rayon of Azerbaijan .
