Gun n ' Rose is a 1992 Hong Kong action film directed by Clarence Fok and starring Alan Tang , Andy Lau , Leon Lai and Simon Yam .
Ip Man 2 ( classified under the name Ip Man 2 : Legend of the Grandmaster in the US ) is a 2010 Hong Kong biographical martial arts film loosely based on the life of Ip Man , a grandmaster of the martial art Wing Chun .
The Five Days was director Dario Argento 's first box office failure in Italy .
The Demi - Bride is a 1927 film directed by Robert Z. Leonard , depicting the naughtiness synonymous with Paris at the time .
The Education of Shelby Knox is 2005 documentary film that tells the coming - of - age story of public speaker and feminist Shelby Knox , a teenager who joins a campaign for comprehensive sex education in the high schools of Lubbock , Texas .
Old Fort Duquesne , or , Captain Jack , the Scout is an historical novel by the American writer Charles McKnight ( 1826 - 1881 ) set in 1750s Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania .
The Forgotten Frontier ( 1931 ) is a documentary film about the Frontier Nursing Service , nurses on horseback , who traveled the back roads of the Appalachian Mountains of eastern Kentucky .
Children of Paradise is set in the theatrical world of Paris during the July Monarchy ( 1830 - -48 ) , centred on the area around the Funambules theatre , situated on the Boulevard du Temple -- pejoratively referred to as the `` Boulevard du Crime '' .
Gustav Altenhain ( December 5 , 1891 in Sprockhövel ( Sauerland ) - December 23 , 1968 in Gevelsberg ( Sauerland ) ) was a German publisher and politician of the Free Democratic Party ( FDP ) .
Ernst Ulrich von Weizsäcker ( born 25 June 1939 in Zürich , Switzerland ) is a German scientist and politician ( SPD ) .
The Vinctiplicata is a clade of Scalidophora uniting the Loricifera and the Priapulida , and representing the sister group to the Kinorhyncha .
Prosomphax is a very small genus in the geometer moth family ( Geometridae ) .
The Tami River rainbowfish ( Glossolepis pseudoincisus ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
In a classification of orchids that was published in 2015 , the genera Brownleea and Disperis constituted the subtribe Brownleeinae of the tribe Orchideae .
The Atlantic sawtail catshark ( Galeus atlanticus ) is a little - known species of catshark , part of the family Scyliorhinidae , found in a small area of the northeastern Atlantic Ocean , centered on the Strait of Gibraltar and the Alborán Sea .
Regalecus is a fish genus of the family Regalecidae , commonly called oarfish , with these currently recognized species :
The Whitaker 's skink , Oligosoma whitakeri ( formerly Cyclodina whitakeri ) , is a threatened species of skink in the Scincidae family .
Leucosidea sericea is a member of the Rosaceae , also known as the rose family .
Triakis is a genus of houndsharks in the family Triakidae .
The New Zealand flatworm ( Arthurdendyus triangulatus ) is a large land flatworm native to New Zealand .
Coppernose barb ( Raiamas christyi ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Raiamas who are found in the Congo River system in Africa .
Bravaisia is a genus in family Acanthaceae .
The Bistonini are a tribe of geometer moths in subfamily the Ennominae .
Stichoneuron is a genus in the family Stemonaceae described as a genus in 1883 .
Morelia spilota cheynei , or the jungle carpet python , is a python subspecies found in the rainforests of Queensland , Australia .
The Iphis monarch ( Pomarea iphis ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
The Duckwater pyrg , scientific name Pyrgulopsis aloba , is a species of very small freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Delturinae are a subfamily of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Loricariidae , including two genera , Delturus and Hemipsilichthys .
Gerris is a bug genus in the family Gerridae ( water striders ) .
According to Mateus and Antunes ( 2001 ) , Draconyx loureiroi is a member of the Iguanodontia , more specifically the Camptosauridae , based on the maxillary teeth , which have a strong vertical primary ridge on the distal side of the labial crown , and the femur , which is curved and has a prominent lesser trochanter .
Paratrichapus sechellarum is a species of beetle in the family Ciidae , the only species in the genus Paratrichapus .
The Lebombo flat lizard ( Platysaurus lebomboensis ) is a species of lizard in the Cordylidae family .
Tula virus ( TULV ) is a single - stranded , negative - sense RNA virus species of Hantavirus first isolated from a European common vole ( Microtus arvalis ) found in Central Russia .
Blanfordia is a genus of terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Talinum is a genus of herbaceous succulent plants in the family Talinaceae ( formerly in the family Portulacaceae ) whose common names include fameflower and flameflower .
The Colobinae are a subfamily of the Old World monkey family that includes 59 species in 10 genera , including the black - and - white colobus , the large - nosed proboscis monkey , and the gray langurs .
The Nicaraguan seed finch ( Oryzoborus nuttingi ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
The Checklist of Australian Lepidoptera synonymised Dasygaster nephelistis with Leucania obumbrata , but made no attempt to assign the species to a genus .
Caribbean reef squid ( Sepioteuthis sepioidea ) , commonly called reef squid , are small 20 cm ( 7.9 in ) torpedo - shaped squid with undulating fins that extend nearly the entire length of the body .
Cavalier - Smith , in a collaborative paper with Alexandra Stechmann , postulated that Apusozoa belongs in the bikont clade .
Homalopterus atrovirens is a species of beetle in the family Megalopodidae , the only species in the genus Homalopterus .
Lyle 's flying fox ( Pteropus lylei ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
The Devils Hole pupfish ( Cyprinodon diabolis ) is a species of fish native to Devils Hole , a geothermal ( 92 ° F or 33 ° C ) , aquifer - fed pool within a limestone cavern , in the Amargosa Pupfish Station of the Desert National Wildlife Refuge Complex east of Death Valley National Park .
Geobius pubescens is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Geobius .
Agassiz 's perchlet ( Ambassis agassizi ) , also known as Agassiz 's glassfish is a species of fish in the Ambassidae family .
Lasaeola is a tangle web spider genus in the family Theridiidae .
Warren 's tree frog , Hyla warreni , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Guyana and possibly Brazil and Venezuela .
Beyrichoceras is a genus belonging to the Goniatitid family , Muensteroceratidae , a group of ammonoids , extinct shelled cephalopods related to belemnites and recent coleoids and more distantly to the nautiloids
Hatiora is a small genus of epiphytic cacti which belongs to the tribe Rhipsalideae within the subfamily Cactoideae of the Cactaceae .
Dwarf tarantulas , also known as sheet funnel - web spiders are a type of spider from the family Mecicobothriidae .
The Terek sandpiper ( Xenus cinereus ) is a small migratory Palearctic wader species , the only member of the genus Xenus .
Baird 's trogon ( Trogon bairdii ) is a species of bird belonging to the Trogonidae family ( Trogoniformes ) .
Crepipora is an extinct genus of marine bryozoan belonging to the Ceramoporidae family .
Turbonillinae is a subfamily of mostly minute parasitic sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Merycochoerus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore of the family Merycoidodontidae ( oreodont ) , endemic to North America during the Late Oligocene to Early Miocene ( 28.4 - -16.3 mya ) existing for approximately 12.1 million years .
The Lord Derby 's parakeet ( Psittacula derbiana ) , also known as Derbyan parakeet , is a monotypic parrot species , which is confined to small pocket of moist evergreen forest in the hills of the Indian state of Arunachal Pradesh and the adjoining parts of Tibet .
Ischnura is a genus of damselflies known as forktails in the family Coenagrionidae .
Mahonia is a genus of about 70 species of evergreen shrubs in the family Berberidaceae , native to eastern Asia , the Himalaya , North America and Central America .
Cryosophileae is a tribe of palms in the subfamily Coryphoideae .
The Pima hardyhead ( Craterocephalus pimatuae ) is a species of fish in the Atherinidae family endemic to Papua New Guinea .
Kristin 's false shieldback ( Acilacris kristinae ) is a tettigoniid orthopteran that is endemic to two localities within Malta Forest in Limpopo , South Africa .
Protocardia is an extinct genus of saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
Pearson 's long - clawed shrew ( Solisorex pearsoni ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Avenionia is a genus of small freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Chamaecostus is a group of plants in the Costaceae described as a genus in 2006 .
The Chatham gerygone or Chatham Island warbler ( Gerygone albofrontata ) is a species of bird in the Acanthizidae family .
Phlomis is a genus of over 100 species of herbaceous plants , subshrubs and shrubs in the family Lamiaceae , native from the Mediterranean region east across central Asia to China .
Cocoharpinia iliffei is a species of crustacean in the family Phoxocephalidae .
Leptomitales are an order of water moulds within the class Oomycetes that contains the genus Apodachlya , belonging to the kingdom Protista .
Stylosanthes is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae and contains numerous highly important pasture and forage species .
The Mixe tree frog , Megastomatohyla mixe , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Mexico .
Dodecahema is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with a single species restricted to California , where it is an endangered species on the state and federal levels .
Buliminus , is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Enidae .
Scarlett 's shearwater ( Puffinus spelaeus ) was a species of seabird in the petrel family Procellariidae .
Zophochroa was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered to be a synonym of Elaphristis .
The Threadtail conger ( Uroconger syringinus , also known as the Slender - tail conger ) is an eel in the family Congridae ( conger / garden eels ) .
The Japanese amberjack or yellowtail , Seriola quinqueradiata , is a bony fish in the family Carangidae .
Aturia is an extinct genus of Paleocene to Miocene nautilids within Aturiidae , a monotypic family , established by Campman in 1857 for Aturia Bronn , 1838 , and is included in the superfamily Nautilaceae in Kümmel 1964 .
The Tachinidae are a large and variable family of true flies within the insect order Diptera , with more than 8,200 known species and many more to be discovered .
Euomphaloceratinae is a subfamily of Upper Cretaceous ammonites included in the Acanthoceratidae , characterized by generally evolute shells with quadrate whorl sections that are strongly ribbed .
The Cape ground squirrel ( Xerus inauris ) is found in most of the drier parts of southern Africa from South Africa , through to Botswana , and into Namibia .
Mimiptera fulvella is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Mimiptera .
Misszhouia is a genus of small to average sized ( up to 6 centimetres ( 2.4 in ) long ) marine arthropods within the Naraoiidae family , that lived during the early Cambrian period .
Nosoderma diabolicum ( formerly Phloeodes diabolicus ) is a beetle of the Family Zopheridae .
Libinia is a genus of crabs in the family Epialtidae , containing twelve extant species :
Gomphodesmidae is a family of millipedes in the order Polydesmida , containing around 55 genera and 150 species .
Cardiomera genei is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Cardiomera .
Tereingaornis moisleyi , also referred to as Moisley 's penguin , is a genus and species of extinct penguin from the Middle Pliocene of New Zealand .
The Indian giant flying squirrel ( Petaurista philippensis , Gujarati : ઉડતી ખિસકોલી , මහ හම්බාවා in Sinhala ) , alternatively referred to as the large brown flying squirrel or the common giant flying squirrel , is a species of rodent in the Sciuridae family .
Prosthechea flowers are unique among the Laeliinae in producing fluorescent flavenoid crystals when preserved in ethanol with 5 % sodium hydroxide .
Jerdon 's babbler ( Chrysomma altirostre ) is an endangered passerine bird from South Asia .
Arsenophonus is a genus of Enterobacteriaceae , of the Gammaproteobacteria .
The Sind krait ( Bungarus sindanus ) is a species of krait , a venomous elapid snake found in India , Nepal and Pakistan .
Hartogiella is a genus of flowering plant within the family Celastraceae .
The Weyland ringtail possum ( Pseudochirulus caroli ) is a species of marsupial in the family Pseudocheiridae .
Dicheros is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Scarabaeidae , subfamily Cetoniinae .
Merriam 's pocket mouse ( Perognathus merriami ) is a species of rodent in the family Heteromyidae .
Beddome 's coral snake ( Calliophis beddomei ) is a species of venomous elapid snake endemic to hills of peninsular India .
The Lewis 's woodpecker ( Melanerpes lewis ) is a large North American species of woodpecker which ornithologist Alexander Wilson named after Meriwether Lewis , one of the explorers who surveyed the areas bought by the United States of America as part of the Louisiana Purchase .
Didimus is a genus of beetles of the family Passalidae .
The Wilkins 's finch ( Nesospiza wilkinsi ) , also known as Wilkins 's bunting or the grosbeak bunting , is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
The Fox 's weaver ( Ploceus spekeoides ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
The São Tomé thrush or olivaceous thrush also called the Príncipe thrush or Gulf of Guinea thrush ( Turdus olivaceofuscus ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
The Hispaniolan yellow tree frog or common treefrog ( Osteopilus pulchrilineatus ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Hispaniola , where it is found in both the Dominican Republic and Haiti .
Macrophya is a genus of sawfly ( order Hymenoptera , family Tenthredinidae ) .
Agrioceros is a genus of insects in the Ethmiidae family .
The Chthamaloidea are a subdivision of Balanomorpha proposed by Newman and Ross to include barnacles with shell wall composed of rostrum , carina , and one to three pairs of latera , rarely supplemented with one or more whorls of basal imbricating plates .
Magaliella punctata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Magaliella .
Eocnides fragilis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Eocnides .
The Ptychodacteae are a suborder of sea anemones in the order Actiniaria , with these families :
The Philippine gray flying fox ( Pteropus speciosus ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
The Alaska whitefish ( Coregonus nelsonii ) is a species of whitefish in the family Salmonidae .
Isolaboides is a genus of earwigs , the sole member of the subfamily Isolaboidinae .
Sauropodomorpha is one of the two major clades within the order Saurischia .
Hatt 's vesper rat ( Otonyctomys hatti ) , also known as the Yucatán vesper rat , is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Tahiti reed warbler ( Acrocephalus caffer ) is a songbird in the genus Acrocephalus .
The Townsend 's mole ( Scapanus townsendii ) is a fossorial mammal in the family Talpidae , and is the largest North American mole .
Nactus is a genus of geckos endemic to Oceania .
The Mauritius lowland forest day gecko ( Phelsuma guimbeaui guimbeaui Mertens , 1963 ) is a diurnal subspecies of gecko .
The Piura chat - tyrant ( Ochthoeca piurae ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Gallagher 's free - tailed bat ( Chaerephon gallagheri ) is a free - tailed bat endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
The Talaud kingfisher ( Todiramphus enigma ) is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae .
The Mrs. Gould 's sunbird ( Aethopyga gouldiae ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
Imaizumi 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus imaizumii ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
Monura is an extinct order of wingless insects in the subclass Apterygota .
Anaphalis is a genus of flowering plants within the Asteraceae family , whose members are commonly known by the name pearl or pearly everlasting .
The Manytooth conger ( Conger triporiceps , also known as the Manytooth conger eel or simply the Conger eel ) is an eel in the family Congridae ( conger / garden eels ) .
The Nodugl tree frog ( Litoria micromembrana ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Euproctus , the European mountain salamanders , is a genus of salamanders in the Salamandridae family from Sardinia and Corsica .
The Mexican funnel - eared bat ( Natalus stramineus ) is a bat species from the northern Lesser Antilles .
The Hispaniola nightjar ( Antrostomus ekmani ) , also known as the Hispaniolan nightjar , was previously considered a subspecies of the Greater Antillean nightjar .
Protocolliuris coerulans is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Protocolliuris .
Kishinouyeidae is a stalked jellyfish family in the order Eleutherocarpida .
The New Britain sparrowhawk ( Accipiter brachyurus ) is a threatened species of bird of prey .
Afrivoluta is a genus of large deepwater sea snails with glossy shells , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Marginellidae , the marginellids .
Sconsia is a genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cassidae , the helmet snails and bonnet snails .
Culladia is a grass moth genus ( family Crambidae ) of subfamily Crambinae , tribe Crambini .
Incilius melanochlorus ( formerly Bufo melanochlorus ; common names : dark green toad , wet forest toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Protoparvovirus is a genus of viruses in the subfamily Parvovirinae of the virus family Parvoviridae .
Leuthneria is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family containing only one species Leuthneria ruficincta , which is known from Sudan .
Neope is a genus of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family found in Asia .
Loxogenius opacipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Loxogenius .
Zosichrysia is a genus or subgenus of moths of the Noctuidae family .
Mopsolodes is an Australian spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) .
Zachrysia is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Camaenidae or Pleurodontidae .
The only species in the genus Quadrasura ktimuna was formerly placed in the genus Asura .
Desmoulin 's whorl snail , scientific name Vertigo moulinsiana , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
Lesueur 's frog ( Litoria lesueurii ) is a species of ground - dwelling tree frog native to south - eastern Australia , from Sydney , New South Wales , to eastern Victoria .
Acheroniotes mlejneki is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Acheroniotes .

The MacGregor 's bowerbird ( Amblyornis macgregoriae ) is a medium - sized , up to 26 cm long , olive brown bowerbird of New Guinea 's mountain forests , roughly the size and shape of a robin .
Lomatus hislopi is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Lomatus .
Euthyneura is a taxonomic clade of snails and slugs , which includes species from freshwater , marine , aquatic and terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the clade Heterobranchia .
The Styrian ringlet ( Erebia stirius , often misspelled `` styrius '' ) is a member of the Satyrinae subfamily of Nymphalidae .
Chrysophtharta is a genus of leaf beetle , family Chrysomelidae .
Holoprizus serratus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Holoprizus .
Pronorites , as for the Pronoritidae , produced discoidal shells with no prominent sculpture , in which the ventral lobe of the suture has three prongs .
Andakhudukia ponomarenkoi is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Andakhudukia .
The Cantharidinae are a taxonomic subfamily of very small to large sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Trochidae , common name top snails .
The Panniet naked - backed fruit bat ( Dobsonia pannietensis ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
The Florida softshell turtle ( Apalone ferox ) is a species of softshell turtle native to the Southeastern United States .
Apristurus is a genus of catshark , the family Scyliorhinidae , commonly known as the ghost or demon catsharks .
Oreomunnea is a genus of two species of flowering plants in the family Juglandaceae , native to southern Mexico and Central America , where they occur in montane rainforest .
Anthocleista was once placed in the family Loganiaceae , but more recent molecular , morphological , and phytochemical evidence has placed the group well within the Gentianaceae .
The Visayan pygmy babbler ( Dasycrotapha pygmaea ) is a bird species endemic to the Philippines .
Streblitinae is a subfamily of Upper Jurassic and Lower Cretaceous ammonites within the family Oppeliidae characterized by compressed , involute shells ; typically oxycones with complex sutures .
Sirembo is a genus of cusk - eels found in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
The Tumbala climbing rat ( Tylomys tumbalensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Berthella is a genus of sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pleurobranchidae .
Polychalca is a genus of tortoise beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae .
The Sick 's swift ( Chaetura meridionalis ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Bartrumella is a small genus of miniature sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pyramidellidae within the tribe Chrysallidini ( sensu taxonomy by Bouchet & Roctroi , 2005 ) .
The Kermadec scalyfin , Parma alboscapularis , is a damselfish of the genus Parma , found around New Zealand 's Kermadec Islands around depths of between 3 and 20 m , over shallow rocky reef areas .
Scissurella is a genus of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Scissurellidae , the small slit snails .
Edwardsia is a genus of sea anemones , the type of the family Edwardsiidae .
Rhombosoleinae is a subfamily of fish in the Pleuronectidae family , comprising nine genera and 19 species ; all members of this subfamily are right eye flounders with asymmetrical pelvic fins .
Limax flavus ( syn . Limacus flavus ) , known commonly as the yellow slug or tawny garden slug , is a medium to large species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Limacidae .
Camelini is a tribe of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to Asia , North America , and Africa from the Pliocene to the present .
Epidryos is a group of plants in the family Rapateaceae described as a genus with this name in 1962 .
The Sphinx blenny ( Aidablennius sphynx ) is a species of combtooth blenny , and the only species in the genus Aidablennius .
The Shaggy parasol is the common name for three closely related species of mushroom , Chlorophyllum rhacodes , C. olivieri and C. brunneum , found in North America , Europe and Southern Africa ( the latter species is also found in Australia ) .
Rhinella ceratophrys , formerly Bufo ceratophrys , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Chelonoidis is a genus of turtles in the tortoise family .
O. aubrevillei was originally named Oktoknema okoubaka and placed in the Octoknemaceae or Olacaceae ; however careful morphological studies of the fruits have led to it being classified as Okoubaka and placed in the Santalaceae .
Hedychium is a genus of flowering plants in the ginger family Zingiberaceae , native to lightly wooded habitats in Asia .
Peregrinella is an extinct genus of brachiopods belonging to the family Peregrinellidae .
The Manu short - tailed bat ( Carollia manu ) is a bat species found in Peru and Bolivia .
The Steganinae Hendel , 1917 , is the smaller of two subfamilies in the fruit fly family Drosophilidae .
Laterallus is a genus of birds in the rail family Rallidae .
Asfaltomylos is an extinct genus of the primitive mammal subclass Australosphenida from the middle Jurassic of Argentina .
Pachylinae is the most diverse subfamily of the harvestman family Gonyleptidae , including around 400 valid species .
Karimi 's fat - tailed mouse opossum ( Thylamys karimii ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
The Venus ' flower basket , or Euplectella aspergillum is a hexactinellid sponge in the phylum Porifera inhabiting the deep ocean .
Heterocentrotus is a genus of slate pencil urchins , part of the familia Echinometridae .
Syngagrella bistriata is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Sincorá antwren ( Formicivora grantsaui ) is a small passerine bird of the genus Formicivora in the family Thamnophilidae , the typical antbirds .
Terpios is a genus of demosponges belonging to the family Suberitidae .
Roosmalen 's dwarf porcupine , Sphiggurus roosmalenorum , is a porcupine species from the New World porcupine family endemic to northern Brazil .
The Tibetan antelope or chiru ( Pantholops hodgsonii ) ( Tibetan : གཙོད་ , Wylie : gtsod , pronounced ( tsǿ ) ; Chinese : 藏羚羊 ; pinyin : zàng língyáng ) is a medium - sized bovid native to the Tibetan plateau .
Pelargonium zonate spot virus ( PZSV ) is a plant pathogenic virus , classified in the bromoviridae family , genus Anulavirus
Actephila is a genus of the family Phyllanthaceae , first described as a genus in 1826 .
The Prioninae are a subfamily of Cerambycidae ( long - horned beetles ) .
Xianguangia is a soft - bodied actinia - like fossil animal from the Chengjiang Biota of China .
Uromyrtus is a genus of plants in the myrtle family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1941 .
Perisesarma is a genus of mangrove crabs in the family Sesarmidae ( or Grapsidae in some classifications ) predominantly found in the Indo - Pacific .
The Quissange forest tree frog , Leptopelis marginatus , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family endemic to Angola .
Chrysanthia is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Oedemeridae subfamily Nacerdinae .
Naseus is an extinct genus of surgeonfishes belonging to the family Acanthuridae .
Aldabrica fryeri is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Aldabrica .
Mealworms are the larval form of the mealworm beetle , Tenebrio molitor , a species of darkling beetle .
The Sardinian dhole ( Cynotherium sardous ) , also known as the Sardinian fox , was an endemic insular canid , that occurred on the Mediterranean islands of Sardinia ( which currently belongs to Italy ) and Corsica ( which currently belongs to France ) .
The California towhee ( Melozone crissalis ) is a bird of the family Emberizidae , native to the coastal regions of western Oregon and California in the United States and Baja California Sur in Mexico .
Sun squirrels ( genus Heliosciurus ) , form a taxon of squirrels under the subfamily Xerinae and the tribe Protoxerini .
The Santa Marta mountain tanager ( Anisognathus melanogenys ) , also known as the black - cheeked mountain tanager , is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
Major 's tufted - tailed rat ( Eliurus majori ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Austrophanes robustum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Austrophanes .
Podocarpus ( /ˌpoʊdəˈkɑrpəs/ ; from the Greek , podos , meaning `` foot '' , and karpos , meaning `` fruit '' ) is a genus of conifers , the most numerous and widely distributed of the podocarp family , Podocarpaceae .
The Fulvus roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros fulvus ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Fuller 's caecilian ( also Kuttal caecilian ) , Chikila fulleri , is a species of caecilian endemic to India ; the type specimen was collected six miles southwest of Silchar in Cachar , Assam , at an altitude of about 100 m above sea level .
Bundibugyo virus ( abbreviated BDBV ) was first described in 2008 as a single member of a suggested new species Bundibugyo ebolavirus , which was suggested to be included into the genus Ebolavirus , family Filoviridae , order Mononegavirales .
Monjurosuchus has been placed in the family Monjurosuchidae along with Philydrosaurus , but the relationships of early choristoderes remains unclear .
The Pinacocerataceae are generally smooth , compressed , evolute to involute ammonoids from the Triassic , belonging to the Ceratitida , in which the suture is ammonitic , with adventitious and auxiliary elements .
Melissa 's yellow - eared bat ( Vampyressa melissa ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Sometimes considered the only genus of the family Mirocarididae , Mirocaris is usually placed in the family Alvinocarididae .
The Burmese roofed turtle ( Batagur trivittata ) is one of six species of turtle in the genus Batagur of the Geoemydidae family .
The Ciscaucasian hamster ( Mesocricetus raddei ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Egyptian pipistrelle ( Pipistrellus deserti ) is a species of vesper bat .
Caxamarca is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
The genus Microzada is a genus of moths of the subfamily Chloephorinae and the family Nolidae .
Phryneta is a genus of flat - faced longhorn beetles belonging to the family Cerambycidae .
Paradentobunus aureomaculatus is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Bernaya is a genus of sea snails or cowries , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Hemicrambe is a genus of flowering plants in the family Brassicaceae , comprising two species :
The Boarmiini ( also often called Cleorini ) are a large tribe of geometer moths in the Ennominae subfamily .
The Iriomote cat ( Prionailurus bengalensis iriomotensis ) is a subspecies of the leopard cat living exclusively on the Japanese island of Iriomote .
The Tibetan bunting ( Emberiza koslowi ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .
Latridopsis ciliaris , the Blue moki , is a species of trumpeter native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean around New Zealand and occasionally off southeastern Australia at depths of 10 metres ( 33 ft ) and greater .
Zhenyuanlong has been placed in the family Dromaeosauridae .
Mokola virus ( MOKV ) is a member of the Lyssavirus genus , which belongs to the family Rhabdoviridae .
The Palenque poison frog ( Ameerega erythromos ; formerly Epipedobates erythromos ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family endemic to Ecuador .
Deroplatyini is a tribe of the subfamily Deroplatyinae of the family Mantidae of Mantodea .
Phylloboletellus is a genus of bolete fungi in the Boletaceae family .
Paurodontidae is a family of Late Jurassic to Early Cretaceous mammals in the order Dryolestida .
The Nhandiroboideae are a paraphyletic basal group of genera in the Cucurbitaceae , or gourd family , of flowering plants .
The Hume 's short - toed lark or Hume 's lark ( Calandrella acutirostris ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
The Kai stingaree ( Urolophus kaianus ) is a species of stingray in the family Urolophidae , known only from two juveniles collected from 236 m ( 774 ft ) deep in the Kai Islands of eastern Indonesia .
The Italian agile frog ( Rana latastei ) also known as the Lataste 's frog , is a true frog endemic to the plains of northern Italy , the extreme southern tip of Switzerland , the Istrian region of Slovenia , and adjacent Croatia .
Menoceras ( `` Crescent Horns '' ) is a genus of extinct , small rhinoceros endemic to most of southern North America and ranged as far south as Panama during the early Miocene epoch .
Raymondaspis is a genus of trilobites in the family Styginidae .
Riograndia is currently classified as a basal genus in the family Tritheledontidae .
Poecilia is a genus of fishes in the family Poeciliidae of the order Cyprinodontiformes .
The Lagos serotine ( Eptesicus platyops ) is a species of vesper bat .
Astropecten is a genus of sea stars of the family Astropectinidae .
The Cozumelan golden bat ( Mimon cozumelae ) is a bat species from Central and northern South America .
Rhodothyrsus is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae , first described as a genus in 1999 .
Richeria is a genus of flowering plant belonging to the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1797 .
The Stenochilidae are a spider family with twelve described species in two genera .
Acrymia is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1908 .
Corypha ( Gebang Palm , Buri Palm and Talipot Palm ) is a genus of palms ( family Arecaceae ) , native to India , Malaysia , Indonesia , the Philippines , New Guinea , northeastern Australia ( Cape York Peninsula , Queensland ) .
Senegalia schlechteri ( as Acacia schlechteri ) .
The Choctaw bean , scientific name Villosa choctawensis , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Unionidae .
Empedaula is a genus of moth in the family Gelechiidae , similar to Aristotelia .
Phygelius , common names Cape fuchsia or Cape figwort , is a genus of flowering plants in the Scrophulariaceae family , native to wet slopes and banks in southern Africa .
Ralfsiaceae is a family of brown algae in the order Ralfsiales .
Daucus is a worldwide genus of herbaceous plants of the family Apiaceae of which the best - known species is the cultivated carrot .
The Campo Grande tree frog , Hypsiboas cymbalum , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
Salmonidae is a family of ray - finned fish , the only living family currently placed in the order Salmoniformes .
Siraitia is a genus of plants from the Cucurbitaceae family .
Limestone Canyon virus ( LSC ) is a single - stranded , negative - sense RNA zoonotic Hantavirus that is genetically similar to Sin Nombre virus which causes Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome ( HPS ) in humans .
The Banda myzomela ( Myzomela boiei ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
The New Guinea long - eared bat ( Nyctophilus microtis ) is a species of vesper bat .
Gourlayia regia is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Gourlayia .
The New Zealand piper ( Hyporhamphus ihi ) is a halfbeak found all around New Zealand in shallow inshore waters .
Orbeopsis is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1978 .
Cowan 's shrew tenrec ( Microgale cowani ) is a species of mammal in the family Tenrecidae .
The Italian edible frog ( Pelophylax kl . hispanicus ) is a hybridogenic species in the true frog family Ranidae .
Ptychopyxis is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae first described in 1861 .
Ptilodontidae is a family of primitive mammals within the extinct order Multituberculata .
Celtis occidentalis , commonly known as the common hackberry , is a large deciduous tree native to North America .
Stylulus nasutus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Stylulus .
The Saipan reed warbler ( Acrocephalus hiwae ) is a critically endangered songbird of the Mariana Islands .
The Arnhem leaf - nosed bat ( Hipposideros inornatus ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
The Western limestone ctenotus ( Ctenotus australis ) is a species of skink native to coastal areas of south west Western Australia .
The Central American river turtle ( Dermatemys mawii ) also known locally as the `` hickatee '' or tortuga blanca ( white turtle ) is the only living species in the family Dermatemydidae .
Acanthoxyla is included in the family Phasmatidae .
Heteropteryx dilatata , also known as jungle nymph , Malaysian stick insect , Malayan jungle nymph , or Malayan wood nymph , is a large member of the Phasmatodea , commonly kept in captivity .
Valcouroceras is the type genus for the Valcouroceratidae , a family in the nautiloid order Oncocerida named by Rousseau Flower , 1943 , named for Valcour Island in Lake Champlain , between New York state and Vermont , where it was first discovered .
Sundevall 's roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros caffer ) , also called Sundevall 's leaf - nosed bat , is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Cladistic analyses showed that Emausaurus was a basal member of the Thyreophora , more derived than Scutellosaurus , but less than Scelidosaurus .
Lepidopetalum is a genus of six species of trees known to science , constituting part of the plant family Sapindaceae .
Euomphaloceras is an early Upper Cretaceous ammonite genus , ( Cephalopoda , Ammonoidea ) , included in the Acanthoceratinae until established as the type genus for the Euomphaloceratinae by Cooper , 1978 .
The Yunnan nuthatch ( Sitta yunnanensis ) is a species of nuthatch endemic to South - Western China .

The Brazilian blind electric ray , Benthobatis kreffti , is a species of fish in the Narcinidae family endemic to Brazil .
Martelella is a genus of Gram - negative , oxidase- and catalase - positive , strictly aerobic , non - spore - forming bacteria from the family of Aurantimonadaceae .
Bonnerichthys is a genus of fossil fishes within the family Pachycormidae that lived during the Late Cretaceous Period Fossil remains of this taxon are known from the Smoky Hill Member of the Niobrara Chalk Formation of Kansas ( Late Coniacian - Early Campanian , about 87 - 81 million years ago ) .
Zerdana is an Iranian endemic and monotypic genus in family Brassicaceae with the single species of Zerdana anchonioides Boiss .
Benueites is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus from the Upper Cretaceous named by Revment , 1954 , included in the family Collignoniceratidae , superfamily Acanthocerataceae .
The Sicilian wall lizard ( Podarcis waglerianus ) is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .
Based on his observations and comparison with the notes of Lewis and Clark , Merriam assessed that the Columbian ground squirrel was not a variant of the Arctic ground squirrel , but a separate species , which he named as Spermophilus columbianus , rejecting the genus designation Arctomys and reapplying the species designation originally applied by Ord in 1815 .
The Aru flying fox ( Pteropus aruensis ) is a Critically Endangered species of megabat found in the Aru Islands in Indonesia .
Mecaspis is a genus of cylindrical weevils belonging to the family Curculionidae .
The Freshwater blenny , ( Salaria fluviatilis ) , is a species of fish in the Blenniidae family .
The Japanese lates ( Lates japonicus ) , also known as the akame ( from the Japanese 赤目 , アカメ , literally `` red eye '' ) or Japanese barramundi , is a rare and shy fish endemic to Japan .

The Antioquia bristle tyrant ( Phylloscartes lanyoni ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .

Galearia is a genus of plant of the family Pandaceae .
The Enggano hill myna or Enggano myna ( Gracula enganensis ) is a member of the starling family .
Xiphopteris is a defunct genus of ferns in the family Polypodiaceae .
Holcorpidae is a small family of extinct insects in the scorpionfly order Mecoptera , which contains a single genus , Holcorpa .
Diplolaemus darwinii , commonly known as Darwin 's iguana , is a species of lizard native to the southern tip of South America .
Markuelia is a genus of fossil worm - like bilaterian animals allied to Ecdysozoa and known from strata of Lower Cambrian to Lower Ordovician age containing five species .
Agrostemma is a genus of annual plants in the Caryophyllaceae family , containing the species known as corncockles .
The Cape golden mole ( Chrysochloris asiatica ) is a small , insectivorous mammal of the family Chrysochloridae , the golden moles .
Aktjubocheilus is an oncocerid Nautiloidea genus from the Upper Devonian ( M Famenian ) included in the Acleistoceratidae , a family characterized by depressed , or rarely compressed , exogastric brevicones and cyrtocones .
Herpetocetus is a genus of cetotheriid mysticete in the subfamily Herpetocetinae .
The Cameroon olive pigeon ( Columba sjostedti ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Plusiinae is a smallish ( for noctuid standards ) subfamily of the moth family Noctuidae .
Ipomopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the phlox family , Polemoniaceae .
The Hookeriaceae are a family of mainly tropical mosses of the order Hookeriales .
Mammea is a flowering plant genus with about 50 species in the family Calophyllaceae .
Major 's long - tailed tenrec ( Microgale majori ) is a species of mammal in the family Tenrecidae .
Endospermum is a genus of plants , under the family Euphorbiaceae and the monotypic subtribe Endosperminae first described as a genus in 1861 It is native to E + S + SE Asia , Papuasia , Queensland , and certain islands of the W Pacific .
Formiscurra is a genus of planthopper in the family Caliscelidae with a single species Formiscurra indicus found in southern India .
Zygnematophyceae is a class of green algae in the division Charophyta .
Argema is a genus of moths from the Saturniidae family , commonly known as moon moths .
Odontostomus is a genus of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Odontostomidae .
Pedicularia is a genus of small predatory or ectoparasitic sea snails , cowry - like marine gastropod molluscs in the family Pediculariidae , the cowry allies .
The Celeuthetini are a weevil tribe in the subfamily Entiminae .
Akiyoshia is a genus of freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Amnicolidae .
Neslia is a plant genus in the mustard family ( Brassicaceae ) .
The Northern Palawan tree squirrel ( Sundasciurus juvencus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Scottish red deer ( Cervus elaphus scoticus ) is a subspecies of red deer , which is native to the British Isles .
Arsinoitheriidae is a family of extinct hoofed mammals belonging to the extinct order Embrithopoda .

The Castelnau 's antshrike ( Thamnophilus cryptoleucus ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Phasiinae is a subfamily of flies in the family Tachinidae .

Sticholotidinae is a beetle subfamily in the family Coccinellidae ( ladybirds ) .

The southern pike ( Esox cisalpinus ) is a freshwater fish restricted to freshwater habitats in central and northern Italy ( Southern Europe ) .
Crossley 's vanga ( Mystacornis crossleyi ) , also known as Crossley 's babbler - vanga , Crossley 's babbler , or Madagascar groundjumper , is a bird species in the family Vangidae .
The California moray ( Gymnothorax mordax ) is a moray eel of the family Muraenidae , found in the eastern Pacific at depths to 40 m. Its length is up to 152 cm . They live up to 30 years and have no pelvic or pectoral fins , or gill covers .
The Spotted drum or spotted ribbonfish ( Equetus punctatus ) , is a species of marine fish in the family Sciaenidae .
Duntroonornis parvus , also referred to as the Duntroon penguin , is a genus and species of extinct penguin from the Late Oligocene of New Zealand .
Crinodendron is a botanic genus with 8 species of flowering plants belonging to the family Elaeocarpaceae .
The Natal hinge - back tortoise ( Kinixys natalensis ) is a species of turtle in the Testudinidae family .
The Carolina anole ( Anolis carolinensis ) is an arboreal lizard found primarily in the southeastern United States and some Caribbean islands .
Actinote is a genus of butterflies from South America of the subfamily Heliconiinae in the family Nymphalidae .
The Yemen linnet was formerly placed in the genus Carduelis but was moved to the genus Linaria based on a phylogenetic analysis of mitochondrial and nuclear DNA sequences .
The West African seahorse ( Hippocampus algiricus ) is a species of fish in the Syngnathidae family ( Seahorses and pipefish ) .
Celtencrinurus is a trilobite in the order Phacopida that existed during the upper Ordovician in what is now Northern Ireland .

Orcuttia is a genus of grass in the family Poaceae .

The Dayak roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros dyacorum ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
The Textulariida are an order of Foraminifera that produce agglutinated shells or tests .

The Sonoran collared lizard , Crotaphytus nebrius , is a collared lizard found in Arizona and Mexico .
Semiannuloceras is an extinct genus of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod of the family Baltoceratidae that lived in what would be Europe during the Ordovician from 490 - -460 mya , existing for approximately 6 million years .

Ivan Grubišić ( born 20 June 1936 ) is a retired Croatian Roman Catholic priest , sociologist , and former independent representative in the Croatian Parliament .
In the June 2009 elections , Véronique De Keyser was elected for her third mandate as member of the European Parliament , and at the same time beginning her first mandate as Vice - President of the Socialists and Democrats ( S&D ) Group .
Tim Greimel is a member of the Michigan House of Representatives , elected in a special election in 2012 to fill a vacancy created by the resignation of Tim Melton .
Winthrop Rockefeller ( May 1 , 1912 -- February 22 , 1973 ) was an American politician and philanthropist , who served as the first Republican Governor of Arkansas since Reconstruction .

Raimondas Vainoras ( born 16 July 1965 ) is a retired Lithuanian football defender , who last played for Auda Riga in Latvia during his professional career .

Charlie Fajkus ( born March 4 , 1957 in the United States ) is a retired American soccer midfielder who spent six seasons in the North American Soccer League and five in the Major Indoor Soccer League .

Camassia howellii , commonly known as Howell 's Camas , is a species of perennials endemic to western Oregon .
Helix obruta is a species of large , edible , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Hapalodectidae ( literally `` soft biters '' hapalos = `` soft , tender , '' dêktês = `` biter '' ) is an extinct family of relatively small - bodied ( 1 - - to 8-kg ) mesonychian placental mammals from the Paleocene and Eocene of North America and Asia .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Marisolaris ansata .
It was described by Houlbert in 1918 , and contains the single species Ircila hecacte .
Heteroteuthis weberi is a species of bobtail squid native to the Indo - Pacific waters off central Indonesia .

The tortrix moth genus Pammene belongs to the tribe Grapholitini of subfamily Olethreutinae .
Cladosporium elegans is a fungus species in the genus Cladosporium ( Anamorphic Davidiella ) .
Metasequoia foxii is an extinct redwood species in the family Cupressaceae described from numerous fossils of varying growth stage .
Murmidius estriatus is a species of beetle from the Cerylonidae family .
Ribes niveum is a North American species of currant known by the common names snowy gooseberry , white - flowered gooseberry , or snow currant .
Pachliopta mariae is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae that is found in the Philippines .
Plectranthias whiteheadi , Whitehead 's basslet , is a species of fish in the Serranidae family occurring in the Western Pacific .
Cupressocrinites is an extinct genus of crinoid from the Middle to Late Devonian of Asia , Australia , Europe , Morocco , and North America .
Heliomeris obscura is a rare Mexican species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Carex buxbaumii is a species of sedge known by the common name club sedge or Buxbaum 's sedge .
Rhamphichthys is a genus of sand knifefishes found in South America .
Fatsia japonica ( fatsi , paperplant or Japanese aralia ; syn . Aralia japonica Thunb . , A. sieboldii Hort . ex K.Koch ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Araliaceae , native to southern Japan and South Korea .
Acacia pravissima ( Ovens wattle or wedge - leaved wattle ) , is a species of evergreen shrub in the Fabaceae family native to Victoria , the South West Slopes and Southern Tablelands of New South Wales , Australia .
Conus zonatus , common name the zoned cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Restrepia sanguinea , the Blood Red Restrepia , is a species of orchid endemic to Venezuela .
Oxychilus lineolatus is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oxychilidae , the glass snails .
Aceria malherbae is a species of gall mite known as the bindweed gall mite .
Cheiracanthium oncognathum is a spider species found in Europe and Russia .
Brachydeiroidea is a superfamily of small to moderately large - sized arthrodire placoderms from the Late Devonian of Europe and Eastern North America .
Carex raynoldsii is a species of sedge known by the common name Raynolds ' sedge .
It contains the single species Socotrella dolichocnema .
Probatodes plumula is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Probatodes .
Adapidae is a family of extinct primates that primarily radiated during the Eocene epoch between about 55 and 34 million years ago .
Imaclava i m a , common name I m a 's turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Drilliidae .
Pitar morrhuanus , or the false quahog , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
Phacelia curvipes is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , known by the common names Washoe phacelia and Washoe scorpionweed .
Pyrola asarifolia , commonly known as liverleaf wintergreen , bog wintergreen or pink wintergreen , is a plant species of the genus Pyrola native to western North America .
The Pectinoidea are a superfamily of marine bivalve mollusks , including the scallops and thorny oysters ( despite the common name , the latter are not true oysters ) .
Conus flavescens , common name the flame cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Daucus pusillus is a species of wild carrot known by the common names American wild carrot and rattle - snake - weed .
Neoniphon sammara is a species of fish in the squirrelfishes found in the Indo Pacific Ocean
The Lithosiini are a tribe of lichen moths in the Erebidae family .
Antennablennius ceylonensis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Indian ocean , around Sri Lanka .
Melocalamus is a genus of Asian bamboos in the grass family .
Atriplex canescens , chamiso , chamiza , four wing saltbush , four - wing saltbush , and fourwing saltbush , is a species of evergreen shrub in the Amaranthaceae family , which is native to the western and mid - western United States .
Belostemma yunnanense is a species of plant in the Apocynaceae family first described in 1941 .
Liatris spicata var . resinosa is found in the southern part of the species natural range , the variable plants have only 5 or 6 flowers per head and the heads are more widely spaced on the stems , these differences are more pronounced when the plants are found in drier and coastal habitats .

Rhabdoblennius snowi , Snow 's rockskipper or the Snow blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific ocean .
Conus klemae , common name the Clem 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Hemigymnus is a genus of wrasses native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pseudotapesia pilatii .

Nososticta coelestina is an Australian species of damselfly in the family Protoneuridae , commonly known as the green - blue threadtail .

Anisopodus brevis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Gahan in 1892 .

Viola hirta is a species of the plant genus Viola .
The Fabaceae , Leguminosae or Papilionaceae , commonly known as the legume , pea , or bean family , is a large and economically important family of flowering plants .
Cavernularia obesa is a species of marine cnidaria in the family Veretillidae .
Dianthus deltoides ( maiden pink ) is a species of Dianthus native to most of Europe and western Asia .
Ouranopithecus macedoniensis is a prehistoric species of orangutan from the Late Miocene of Greece .
Athoracophorus suteri is a leaf - veined slug , a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial gastropod mollusc in the family Athoracophoridae .
Rhinella proboscidea is a species of small South American toads in the family Bufonidae , common in the Amazon rainforest .

The tribe Ormosieae is one of the subdivisions of the plant family Fabaceae , primarily found in tropical regions of the Americas , but also in southeast Asia and northern Australia .
Chrysopsis delaneyi , DeLaney 's Goldenaster , is one of the endemic species to Florida , recently discovered in the genus Chrysopsis , small group of herbaceous plants of the Aster family - Astereae , known commonly as the Goldenasters and primarily native and restricted to Florida .
Torquigener albomaculosus , or the White - spotted pufferfish , is the twentieth discovered species of the genus Torquigener .
Biotocus turbinatus was a species of land snail , a gastropod in the family Odontostomidae .

Piaya is a small genus of relatively large and long - tailed cuckoos , which occur in Mexico , Central America and South America .

The cochoas ( from cocho , Nepali for Cochoa purpurea ) are medium - sized frugivorous , insectivorous and molluscivorous birds in the genus Cochoa .
Megaraptor ( `` giant thief '' ) is a genus of large tyrannosauroid dinosaur that lived in the Turonian to Coniacian ages of the Late Cretaceous .
Lobelia ( /loʊˈbiːliə , lə-/ ) is a genus of flowering plants comprising 415 species , with a subcosmopolitan distribution primarily in tropical to warm temperate regions of the world , a few species extending into cooler temperate regions .

Anthuroidea is a superfamily of isopod crustaceans , formerly treated as a suborder , Anthuridea .
Zodarion aculeatum is a spider species found in Bulgaria , Romania , Serbia and Macedonia .
Lasmigona compressa is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve in the family Unionidae .
Bulinus jousseaumei is a species of tropical freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ramshorn snails and their allies .
Quintinia serrata , the tawheowheo , is a species of evergreen trees in the genus Quintinia endemic to New Zealand .
It contains only one recognized species , Schiekia orinocensis , native to South America ( Brazil , Bolivia , Colombia , Venezuela , Guyana , Suriname , French Guiana ) .
Tetroplon caudatum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Tetroplon .
Bactromantis tolteca is a species of praying mantis in the genus Bactromantis in the order Mantodea .
Peziza phyllogena , commonly known as the common brown cup or the pig - ear cup , is a species of fungus in the family Pezizaceae .
Seguenzia triteia is a species of very small , deep water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Seguenziidae .
Euphorbia lactea is a species of spurge native to tropical Asia , mainly in India .
Spathiopteryx is an extinct genus of wasp currently comprises a single species Spathiopteryx alavarommopsis .
Gibbidessus chipi is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Gibbidessus .
Cardamyla carinentalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Cardamyla .
Basilosauridae is a paraphyletic family of extinct cetaceans that lived during the late middle to the early late Eocene , known from all continents including Antarctica .
Orthocis alnoides is a species of tree - fungus beetle in Ciidae family which can be found throughout Near East and Croatia .
Melipotis jucunda , the Merry Melipotis Moth , is a species of moth in the Erebidae family .
Malacothamnus abbottii is a rare species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name Abbott 's bushmallow .
Talenkauen ( meaning `` small skull '' in Aonikenk , referring to the proportionally small skull ) is a genus of basal iguanodont dinosaur from the Cenomanian - age Upper Cretaceous Pari Aike Formation of Lake Viedma , Santa Cruz , Argentina .
Allomyces javanicus is a species of fungus from Indonesia .
Cyathostelma is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1885 .
Artemisia californica , also known as California sagebrush , is a species of western North American shrubs in the sunflower family .
Melanorosaurus ( meaning `` Black Mountain Lizard '' , from the Greek melas/μέλας , `` black '' , oros/ὄρος , `` mountain '' + sauros/σαῦρος , `` lizard '' ) , is a genus of basal sauropodomorph dinosaur that lived during the Late Triassic period .
Terebralia palustris , common name the giant mangrove whelk , is a species of brackish - water snail , a gastropod mollusk in the family Potamididae .
Delphinium bicolor is a species of larkspur known as little larkspur and low larkspur .
Pausinystalia johimbe , ( Rubiaceae ) , common name Yohimbe , is a plant species native to western and central Africa ( Nigeria , Cabinda , Cameroon , Congo - Brazzaville , Gabon , Equatorial Guinea ) .
Cometaster pyrula , commonly known as the Faint owl moth or Ying - yang moth , is a species of moth of the Erebidae family .
Scaphosepalum pulvinare is a species of orchid found in Colombia and Ecuador .
Huayangosaurus is a genus of stegosaurian dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic of China .
Pinna rudis , the rough pen shell or spiny fan - mussel , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pinnidae .
The Nose Catasetum ( Catasetum naso ) is a species of orchid found from Colombia to Venezuela .
Escavadodontidae is an extinct family of pangolin - like insectivore mammals which were endemic to North America from the Paleocene 63.3 - -60.2 Ma existing for approximately 3.1 million years ..
Lysimachia iniki is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae known by the common names Wailua River yellow loosestrife and Wailua River island - loosestrife .
Solemya velum , common name the Atlantic awning clam , is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Solemyidae , the awning clams .
Petitclercia is a genus of mollusk from the strigoceratid subfamily Disticocratinae which are included in the ammonitid superfamily Haplocerataceae .
Cercocarpus ledifolius is a North American species of mountain mahogany known by the common name curl - leaf mountain mahogany .
Pronesopupa frondicella is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Pupillidae .
Decaspermum is a genus of the botanical family Myrtaceae , first described as a genus in 1776 .
Monotropastrum humile is a species of myco - heterotrophic plant of the family Ericaceae , distributed throughout eastern Asia , from the Himalayas to the Islands of Japan .
Sutterella is a genus of Gram - negative , anaerobic , nonspore - forming bacteria of the family Sutterellaceae which belongs to the class Betaproteobacteria ; they were isolated from human faeces .
Derris robusta is a tree species in the genus Derris found in India .
Cychropsis paramontana is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae .
It is the only member of the genus Candolleodendron .
Cheiracanthium elegans is a species of spider in the genus Cheiracanthium found in Europe and Central Asia .
Bostrychus expatria is a species of freshwater sleeper goby endemic to Lake Manguao on the island of Palawan in the Philippines .
Pupilla triplicata is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pupillidae .
Physaria didymocarpa is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name common twinpod .
Astragalus anxius is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common names troubled milkvetch and Ash Valley milkvetch .
Prunus malayana is a species of plant in the family Rosaceae .
Metamecynopsis duodecimguttata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Metamecynopsis .
Veronica copelandii is a rare species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Copeland 's speedwell .
Fukuia ooyagii is a species of freshwater snail which has an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Longipteryx is a genus of prehistoric bird which lived during the Early Cretaceous ( Aptian stage , 120.3 million years ago ) .
Myrmecia nobilis is species of ant .
Campylognathoides ( `` curved jaw '' , Strand 1928 ) is a genus of pterosaur , discovered in the Württemberg Lias deposits ( dated to the early Toarcian age ) of Germany ; this first specimen consisted however only of wing fragments .
Rhaphidophora celatocaulis '' is a plant species of the family Araceae .
Amoria maculata , common name Carol 's volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Osedax is a genus of deep - sea siboglinid polychaetes , commonly called boneworms , zombie worms , or bone - eating worms .
Podocarpus elongatus ( Breede River yellowwood ) is a species of conifer in the Podocarpaceae family .
Banksia lemanniana , commonly known as the yellow lantern banksia or Lemann 's banksia , is a species of woody shrub of the family Proteaceae native to Western Australia .
Xanthoconium montaltoense is a species of bolete fungus in the genus Xanthoconium .
The African green pigeon ( Treron calvus ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae , and one of 5 green pigeon species in the Afrotropics .
The single species , Elopteryx nopcsai , is known only from very incomplete material , and therefore is considered a nomen dubium ( `` dubious name '' ) by most paleontologists .
Mastiglanis asopos is a species of three - barbeled catfish .
Didemnum vexillum , the carpet sea squirt , is a species of colonial tunicate in the family Didemnidae .
Platygillellus brasiliensis , the Brazilian sand stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Atlantic coast of Brazil where it can be found at depths of from 1 to 6 metres ( 3.3 to 19.7 ft ) in areas with gravel substrates in which it buries itself almost completely except the eyes and the dorsal finlet .
Calliostoma anseeuwi is a species of medium - sized deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Calliostomatidae .
Phthanophaneron harveyi , the Gulf flashlightfish , is a species of flashlight fish endemic to the Gulf of Mexico where it is found at depths of from 32 to 36 metres ( 105 to 118 ft ) .
Calycoseris is a small genus of two species of annual desert wildflowers in the daisy family , native to western North America in the southwestern United States and Northwestern Mexico .
Cerithiopsis lamyi is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae .
Polemon leopoldi is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Calliostoma trotini is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Calliostomatidae .
Synodontis macrops is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Uganda where it is found in the Aswa River basin .
Springeratus polyporatus is a species of clinid native to the waters around the Indian Ocean islands of Réunion and Mauritius where it can be found from the surface to 15 metres ( 49 ft ) in depth .
Erigeron taipeiensis is a Chinese species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Carex helleri is a species of sedge known by the common name Heller 's sedge .
Bothrideridae is a family of beetles in the suborder Polyphaga .
Meristina is an extinct genus of brachiopod that lived from the Late Ordovician to the Middle Devonian of Asia , Europe , and North America .
Aspidoras is a genus of catfishes of the family Callichthyidae .
Micrurus diastema , commonly known as the variable coral snake , is a species of venomous elapid snake , native to southeastern Mexico and northern Central America .
Rhodanassa io is a moth of the Depressariidae family and only species in the Rhodanassa genus .
Eofelis is an extinct genus of small nimravid ( false saber - toothed cats ) .
Anahoplites is a genus of rather involute , compressed hoplitid ammonites with flat sides , narrow flat or grooved venters , and flexious ribs or striae arising from weak umbilicle tubercles that end in fine dense ventrolateral nodes .
Orconectes shoupi , the Nashville crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Ptychocharax rhyacophila is a species of characin endemic to Venezuela , where it is found in the upper Siapa River .
Acanthostyles is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae described as a genus in 1971 .
Takakkawia is a genus of sponge known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale that reached around 4 cm in height .
Rhododendron spinuliferum is a species of Rhododendron native to Yunnan , southwestern Sichuan , and Guizhou China .
Raorchestes menglaensis ( Zhishihe 's bubble - nest frog or Mengla small treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Crataegus × sinaica is a hawthorn that originated as a hybrid between two other hawthorn species , C. azarolus in series Orientales and C. monogyna in series Crataegus .
Prototheora malawiensis is a species of moth of the Prototheoridae family .
Mimulus glaucescens is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name shieldbract monkeyflower .
Hoplocorypha congica is a species of praying mantis found in Angola and the Congo River region .
Oncorhynchus kawamurae , the black kokanee , or kunimasu in Japanese , is a Japanese species of salmon which was thought to had gone extinct in 1940 , but was discovered to still have a living population in 2010 .
Astragalus holmgreniorum is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common names Holmgren milkvetch and paradox milkvetch .
Conus irregularis , common name the irregular cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Sophronicomimus densepunctatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sophronicomimus .
Anguis , or the slow worm , is a small genus of lizards in the family Anguidae .
Clematis pauciflora is a species of clematis known by the common name ropevine .
Procambarus tenuis is a species of crayfish in the genus Procambarus in the family Cambaridae .
Spumellaria is a radiolarian protists order in the class Polycystinea .
The Pycroft 's petrel ( Pterodroma pycrofti ) is a species of seabird in the Procellariidae family .
Cantheschenia is a genus of filefishes native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Erethistes maesotensis is a species of South Asian river catfish native to Myanmar and Thailand where it is known from Moei River near Mae Sot on the Thai - Burmese border .
The Trionychidae are a taxonomic family of a number of turtle genera commonly known as softshells .
Malacocoris chlorizans ( commonly known as delicate apple capsid ) is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Orthotylinae .
The Sabiá , scientific name Mimosa caesalpiniaefolia , is a species of tree with white flowers , a legume in the Fabaceae family .
Streptolabis hispoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Streptolabis .
It contains only one species , Gerdana caritella , which is found in North America , where it has been recorded from south - eastern Canada and the eastern United States .
Phylogenetic relationships between Bovista nigrescens and species of Lycoperdaceae were established based on ITS and LSU sequence data from north European taxa .
Zodarion abantense is a spider species found in Turkey , Georgia and Russia .
Maxillaria cucullata , the Cowl - carrying Maxillaria , is a species of orchid ranging from Mexico southward into Panama .
Ameles moralesi is a species of praying mantis found in Morocco .
Camptopsestis malayana is a moth in the Drepanidae family and only species in the Camptopsestis genus .
Manduca blackburni , commonly known as Blackburn 's Sphinx Moth , Hawaiian Tomato Hornworm , and Hawaiian Tobacco Hornworm , is a species of moth in the family Sphingidae .
Macellocerus acuminatus is a species of darkling beetles in the subfamily Tenebrioninae .
Rhopilema is a genus of jellyfishes .
Aphalara itadori , the Japanese knotweed psyllid , is a species of psyllid from Japan which feeds on Japanese knotweed ( Fallopia japonica ) .
Salvadori 's seedeater or Salvadori 's serin ( Crithagra xantholaemus ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Microsporum is a genus of fungi that causes tinea capitis , tinea corpus , ringworm , and other dermatophytoses ( fungal infections of the skin ) .
Urodacus manicatus , commonly known as the black rock scorpion , is a species of scorpion belonging to the subfamily Urodacinae ( family Scorpionidae ) .
Prunus glandulosa , called Chinese bush cherry , Chinese plum , and dwarf flowering almond , is a species of shrub tree native to China and long present in Japan .
Burmannia biflora , common name northern bluethread , is a plant species native to Cuba , the Bahamas and to the southeastern United States .
Metopium brownei ( also known as chechem or black poisonwood ) is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Stenaelurillus setosus is a species of jumping spider from Burma .
Vitimopsyche is an extinct genus of Mecopteran which existed in what is now northeastern China during the early Cretaceous period .
Sahyadria is a genus of cyprinid fishes native to India where they are endemic to rivers and streams in the Western Ghats .
Bridouxia leucoraphe is a species of tropical freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Paludomidae .
It contains only one species , Colpocrita diptila , which is found in Brazil .
Isoetes macrospora ( big - spore quillwort ) is a species of quillwort in the Isoetaceae family .
Erythrina fusca is a species of flowering tree in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Pediocactus sileri is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Siler 's pincushion cactus and gypsum cactus ( or gypsum plains cactus ) .
Carabus exiguus exiguus is a black - coloured subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Sichuan , China .
Malacanthus is a small genus of tilefishes native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Erigeron pulchellus ( Robin 's plantain , blue spring daisy , hairy fleabane ) is a North American species of plants in the daisy family .
Ovaloparmena affinis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ovaloparmena .
Clubiona pseudoneglecta is a sac spider species found from Europe to Central Asia .
Nodiscala is a taxonomic genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Epitoniidae , the wentletraps .
Phyllocladus alpinus , the mountain toatoa or mountain celery pine , is a species of conifer in the Podocarpaceae family .
Gentiana lutea ( great yellow gentian ) is a species of gentian native to the mountains of central and southern Europe .
Irvingia malayana , also known as wild almond ( Thai : กระบก ) , is a tropical evergreen tree species in the family Irvingiaceae .
Caulanthus glaucus is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name glaucous wild cabbage .
Ecsenius paroculus is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Lactarius rupestris is a species of mushroom in the Russulaceae family .
Murex carbonnieri , also known as the Carbonnier 's murex , is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
Ctenomorpha gargantua is a species of stick insect endemic to northern Australia .
Rodolia koebelei is a species of ladybird beetle from Australia .
Sciota subcaesiella , the locust leafroller moth , is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae .
Lessertia dentichelis is a spider species found in Europe , Canary Islands , Madeira , Canada and New Zealand .
Amyema pendula , also known as drooping mistletoe or furry drooping mistletoe , is a species of flowering plant , an epiphytic hemiparasitic plant of the family Loranthaceae , found attached to several species of Australian eucalypt and occasionally on some species of Acacia .
Taractichthys is a genus of pomfrets .
The Bengal slow loris ( Nycticebus bengalensis ) or northern slow loris is a strepsirrhine primate and a species of slow loris native to the Indian subcontinent and Indochina .
Pterobunocephalus is a genus of banjo catfishes found in tropical South America .
Archaeoceratops , meaning `` ancient horned face '' , is a genus of basal neoceratopsian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous ( Aptian stage ) of north central China .
Nannosquilla decemspinosa is a species of long - bodied , short - legged Mantis Shrimp .
There is only one known species , Velella velella , in the genus .
Alyssum desertorum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name desert madwort .
Euryoryzomys legatus , also known as the Tarija oryzomys or big - headed rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Euryoryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Bulbophyllum aberrans , known as the Deviating Bulbophyllum , is a species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum .
Neppia is a genus of dugesiid triclad that is found in South America , Subantarctic region , Africa , Tasmania and New Zealand .
Tetralonia fumida , also known as Tetralonia ( Thygatina ) fumida , is a species of bees belonging to the family Apidae subfamily Apinae .
Schoenocrambe linifolia is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names flaxleaf plainsmustard , skeleton mustard , and Salmon River plains - mustard .
Canis is a genus of canids containing seven to 10 extant species .
Ariola ransonneti was placed as a synonym of Ariola coelisigna in Poole ( 1989 ) , it is now treated as a valid species .
Amberboa is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , described as a genus in 1832 .
The St Kilda house mouse ( Mus musculus muralis ) is an extinct subspecies of the house mouse found only on the islands of the St Kilda archipelago of northwest Scotland .
Quercus acerifolia ( also called maple - leaved oak ) is a rare North American species of trees in the beech family .
Chleuastochoerus is an extinct genus in the pig family that lived in the Miocene of Russia and Eastern Asia .
Hieracium greenei ( not to be confused with Hieracium greenii ) is a species of hawkweed known by the common name Greene 's hawkweed .
Brandegea is a monotypic genus containing the single species Brandegea bigelovii , the desert starvine .
Astragalus breweri is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Brewer 's milkvetch .

Mauritia is a genus of fan palms which is native to northern South America and to the Island of Trinidad in the Caribbean .

Rubus wheeleri a North American species of brambles in the rose family .
Myrceugenia colchaguensis is a species of small evergreen tree in the genus Myrceugenia of the family Myrtaceae .
Cleghornia is a genus of plants in the dogbane family ; its various species are distributed in Borneo , China , Laos , Malaysia , Sri Lanka , Thailand , and Vietnam .
There is only one known species , Dielitzia tysonii , endemic to Western Australia .

Pholidophorus is an extinct genus of teleost fish from the Triassic and Jurassic periods of Africa , Europe , and South America .

Vetufebrus is an extinct genus of haemospororida that was described from Dominican amber dating to the mid Tertiary era .
Eryngium ombrophilum is a plant species native to Brazil , the type specimen collected there from the State of Paraná .
Hypsotropa ochricostella is a species of snout moth in the genus Hypsotropa .

It contains only one species , Neosyntaxis warringtonella , which is found in Papua New Guinea .
Stegastes partitus or the bicolor damselfish is a species of bony fish in the family Pomacentridae found near the sea bed on shallow rocky and coral reefs in the Caribbean Sea , the Gulf of Mexico and off the coasts of Florida .

Hamadryas arethusa is a species of cracker butterfly in the family Nymphalidae .
