Paphiopedilum emersonii , described in 1982 , is a species of orchid named after American orchid enthusiast Emerson ' Doc ' Charles .
Magicicada tredecassini is a species of periodical cicada endemic to the United States .
Clarkia breweri is a species of wildflower known by the common names fairy fans and Brewer 's clarkia .
Neopachygaster meromelas , the silver - strips black , is a European species of soldier fly .
Lima lima , or the spiny fileclam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Limidae .
Hymenolepis diminuta , also known as rat tapeworm , is a species of Hymenolepis tapeworm that causes hymenolepiasis .
Dacrydium comosum is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae .
Cirsium quercetorum is a species of thistle endemic to coastal California , its common names include brownie thistle and Alameda thistle .
Longitarsus suturellus is a species of beetle in the subfamily Galerucinae .
The Bahia forest frog , Macrogenioglottus alipioi , is a species of frog in the Odontophrynidae family .
Aipysurus eydouxii , commonly known as the beaded sea snake , marbled seasnake , or spine - tailed seasnake , is a species of sea snake .
Gracula is a genus of mynas , tropical members of the starling family of birds .
Geranium maderense , known as giant herb - Robert or the Madeira cranesbill , is a species of flowering plant in the Geraniaceae family , native to the island of Madeira .
Cottoperca is a genus of thornfishes southern oceans .
Lyncina schilderorum , common names the sandy cowry or Schilder 's cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Plectranthus esculentus , with English common names kaffir potato , and Livingstone potato , is a species of plant in the dicot family Lamiaceae .
Apatomerus ( meaning `` deceptive femur '' ) , is a genus of extinct reptile known from a single fossil ( KUVP 1199 ) from the Albian - age ( Lower Cretaceous ) Kiowa Shale of Kansas , USA .
Eriogonum diatomaceum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Churchill Narrows buckwheat .
Triplophysa gundriseri is a species of stone loach from Mongolia and Tuva ( Russia ) .
Carychium exiguum , common name the obese thorn snail , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the subfamily Carychiinae .

Terminonaris is a genus of extinct pholidosaurid crocodyliforms that lived in the Late Cretaceous ( Cenomanian and Turonian ) .
Quinca mirifica also known as the Sailfin cardinalfish is a species of cardinalfish family Apogonidae and the only member of its genus .
Polysiphonia morrowii is a species of red algae native to Northeast Asia .
Scirpus microcarpus is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common names panicled bulrush , smallfruit bulrush , and barberpole bulrush .
Rhodactis howesii is a species of marine cnidarian in the order Corallimorpharia , a sea anemone - like corallimorph found on reefs in tropical regions of the Pacific Ocean .
Luperosuchus is an extinct genus of crurotarsan , a group which includes crocodilians and their ancestors .
Buddleja cestriflora is a rare species endemic to a small area near the eastern coast of Brazil , where it grows in the cloud forest along roadsides and in wet rocky clearings on the eastern border of Serra Geral of Santa Catarina and Rio Grande do Sul .
Pseudolithoxus anthrax is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Orinoco River basin .
Auxotricha ochrogypsa is a moth in the Elachistidae family , and the only species in the genus Auxotricha .
Gastrocopta moravica is a fossil species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
Metoptomatidae is an extinct family of fossil mollusks from the Paleozoic era .
Amphitrite ornata or ornate worm , is a species of marine polychaete worm in the family Terebellidae .
Phyllostegia velutina is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name velvet phyllostegia .
Vagococcus salmoninarum is a species of bacteria , with type strain NCFB 2777 .
Epithelantha bokei is a species of cactus known by the common names pingpong ball cactus and button - cactus .
Bothriechis supraciliaris , or the blotched palm - pit viper , is a species of venomous snake in the family Viperidae .
Amoria undulata , common name Wavy Volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Trichomonadida is an order of anaerobic protists , included with the parabasalids .
Pseudallescheria boydii is a species of fungus classified in the Ascomycota .
Leukoma staminea , common name the Pacific littleneck clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .

Linanthus filiformis ( formerly Gilia filiformis ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name yellow gilia .
Isotria ( fiveleaf orchid ) is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Leptochiloides is a small nearctic genus of potter wasps known from dry areas in South - Western North America .
Angadenia berteroi , common name pineland golden trumpet , is a plant species in the Apocynaceae , first described in 1844 .
Brachytarsomys villosa ( hairy - tailed antsangy ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Eomamenchisaurus ( meaning `` dawn Mamenchisaurus '' ) is a genus of mamenchisaurid sauropod dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic of Yuanmou , Yunnan , China .
Lipophrys pholis , commonly known as Shanny , is a species of combtooth blenny .
Alicia pretiosa is a sea anemone species in the genus Alicia which can be found in such seas as the Red Sea and South Pacific Ocean .
Eburia brevispinis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Guatemala , Mexico and Nicaragua .
Nebothriomyrmex is a genus of ants in the subfamily Dolichoderinae containing the single species Nebothriomyrmex majeri .
It contains the single species Orthopterygium huaucui , which is endemic to western Peru .
Callitriche terrestris is a species of plant in the Callitrichaceae family found in Canada and in the eastern United States .

Hemianax ephippiger , the vagrant emperor , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Parmelia saxatilis , commonly known as the salted shield lichen or crottle , is a species of foliose lichen in the family Parmeliaceae .
Banksia elegans , commonly known as the elegant banksia , is a species of woody shrub in the genus Banksia of the family Proteaceae .
Gemella sanguinis is a species of bacteria within the genus Gemella .
Ariocarpus fissuratus ( formerly known as Anhalonium fissuratus ) is a species of cactus found in small numbers in northern Mexico and Texas in the United States .
Heteroponera angulata is a species of ant in the genus Heteroponera , endemic to Brazil .
Dodonaea aptera , commonly known as coast hop - bush , is a species of coastal shrub endemic to Western Australia .
Trifolium hybridum , the alsike clover , is a plant species of the genus Trifolium in the pea family Fabaceae .

Parmacella gervaisii is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Parmacellidae .

Trombidium breei is a species of red mite in the genus Trombidium in the family Trombidiidae .

Pinus chiapensis is a pine tree species in the Pinaceae family , and is commonly known as Chiapas pine , in Spanish as pino blanco , pinabete , or ocote .
Nebria pharina is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Tibet .
Eryngium racemosum is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name delta eryngo , or delta button celery .
Pterotyphis eos paupereques is a subspecies of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .

Iberis sempervirens , the evergreen candytuft or perennial candytuft , is a species of flowering plant in the family Brassicaceae , native to southern Europe .

Campanula griffinii is a species of bellflower known by the common name Griffin 's bellflower .
Psaeropterella macrocephala is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Psaeropterella of the family Tephritidae .
Conus natalis , common name the Natal Textile Cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Jaltomata werffii is a plant species endemic to the Galápagos Islands in Ecuador .
Pissarrachampsa ( meaning `` piçarra ( the local name for the sandstones it was recovered from ) crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of baurusuchid mesoeucrocodylian from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .
Scartichthys gigas , the giant blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern Pacific ocean , from Panama to northern Chile .
Bacillus nealsonii is a species of bacteria first isolated from a spacecraft - assembly facility .
Wild apple ( lat . : Malus baccata ) is an Asian species of apple known by the common names Siberian crab apple , Siberian crab , Manchurian crab apple and Chinese crab apple .
Schoenus brevifolius , known as zig - zag bog - rush , is a species of sedge native to Australia , New Zealand , New Caledonia , and the Ogasawara ( Bonin ) Islands .
Dermestes ater is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the skin beetles .
Fabiana imbricata ( pichi ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Solanaceae , native to dry upland slopes in Chile and Argentina .
Acanthops falcataria , common name South American dead leaf mantis , is a species of praying mantis in the subfamily Acanthopinae of the family Acanthopidae and is one of many mantis from various genera that resembles a dead leaf .

Marasmarcha brevirostris is a species of moth in the genus Marasmarcha , known from Guatemala , Mexico , and Panama .

Nangura is a genus of skinks , a type of lizard .

Citropsis articulata , known commonly as the African cherry orange , West African cherry orange , Uganda cherry orange , and locally as omuboro , is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae .
Vanilla tahitensis is a species of orchid in the genus Vanilla .
Cerauromeros is a trilobite in the order Phacopida that existed in what is now Illinois , U.S.A. It was described by Pribyl and Vanek in 1985 , and the type species is Cerauromeros hydei , which was originally described under the genus Ceraurus by Weller in 1907 .
Glyptophysa petiti is a species of small sinistral ( left - handed ) air - breathing freshwater snail , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Planorbidae .
Bidens amplissima ( Vancouver Island beggarticks ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Venyukovioidea is an infraorder of anomodont therapsids from the Permian of Russia .
Neovenatoridae is a family of large carnivorous dinosaurs representing a branch of the allosauroids , a large group of carnosaurs that also includes the sinraptorids , carcharodontosaurids , and allosaurids .
Bangana gedrosicus is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Pakistan where it is only found in the Mashkel River drainage in Baluchistan .

Enterolobium cyclocarpum , commonly known as guanacaste , caro caro , or elephant - ear tree , is a species of flowering tree in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is native to tropical regions of the Americas , from central Mexico south to northern Brazil ( Roraima ) and Venezuela .
Doryphora sassafras , commonly known as Sassafras , Yellow- , Canary- or Golden sassafras , or Golden Deal , is a species of evergreen tree of the family Atherospermataceae native to the subtropical and temperate rainforests of eastern New South Wales and Queensland , Australia .

Tympanocryptis is a genus of Australian lizards from the family Agamidae .

Sarcodon fuscoindicus is a species of tooth fungus in the genus Sarcodon .

The Cocos buff - banded rail , Gallirallus philippensis andrewsi , is an endangered subspecies of the buff - banded rail endemic to the Cocos ( Keeling ) Islands , an Australian Offshore Territory in the central - eastern Indian Ocean .
Python kyaiktiyo , commonly known as the Myanmar short - tailed python , is a species of python found in Myanmar ( Burma ) .
The Indian wild ass or Baluchi wild ass ( Equus hemionus khur ) also called the ghudkhur in the local Gujarati language , is a subspecies of the onager native to Southern Asia .
Dasyloricaria latiura is a species of armored catfish native to Panama and Colombia where it is found in the Tuira and Atrato River basins .
Lima pellucida , or the Antillean file shell , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Limidae .
Chaenomeles cathayensis is a species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Eurycheilichthys is a small genus of armored catfishes native to South America .
Aulichthys japonicus , the Tubenose , is a species of Hypoptychid fish native to shallow waters on the coasts of Japan , China and the Korean Peninsula This species lays its eggs inside of the peribranchial cavities of ascidians .
Amphipteryx agrioides , the montane relict damsel , is a species of damselfly in family Amphipterygidae .
Eledone schultzei , the brush - tipped octopus , is a rare species of octopus .
Penicillium phoeniceum is an anamorph , saprotrophic species of the genus of Penicillium which produces oosporein , phoenicine and phenicin .
Hipparchia azorina , the Azores Grayling , is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Semionotiformes ( `` flag - back form '' ) is an order of primitive , ray - finned , primarily freshwater fish from the Triassic to the Cretaceous .
The Enterobacteriales are an order of Gram - negative bacteria that includes only one family which is the Enterobacteriaceae .
Torreya jackii ( Chinese : 长叶榧树 ; pinyin : fěishù ; literally : `` longleaf torreya '' ) is a species of conifer in the family Cephalotaxaceae .
Xyris drummondii , Drummond 's yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plant in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Mimanancylus borneensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimanancylus .
Decodon verticillatus , the sole species in the genus Decodon , is a flowering plant in the Lythraceae family .
Lonicera caprifolium , the Italian woodbine , perfoliate honeysuckle , goat - leaf honeysuckle , Italian honeysuckle , or perfoliate woodbine , is a species of perennial flowering plants in the genus Lonicera of the Caprifoliaceae family .
Hoploparia longimana is a species of fossil lobsters belonging to the family Nephropidae .
Cyrtodactylus buchardi is a species of gecko recently described from Champasak Province , Laos .
Rhinella chrysophora , sometimes known as the Rio Viejo toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Baumea is a genus of the sedge family , which includes around 30 species native to Madagascar and the Pacific Islands , with 15 species in Australia .
Congoglanis alula is a species of loach catfish found in the Congo River Basin in Angola , the Democratic Republic of Congo and possibly in Zambia .
Tchoiria is a genus of simoedosaurid choristodere , a type of crocodile - like aquatic reptile .
Peptoniphilus is a genus of bacteria in the phylum Firmicutes ( Bacteria ) .
Mycobacterium phage L5 is a bacteriophage known to infect bacterial species of the genus Mycobacterium .
Eriogonum helichrysoides , common names spreading buckwheat and strawflower wild buckwheat , is a plant species endemic to Kansas .
Astragalus sabulonum is a species of milkvetch known by the common name gravel milkvetch .
Humba is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae .
Palaquium luzoniense ( also called Red Nato ) is a species of plant in the Sapotaceae family .
Pentanisia is a genus of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family .
Ytu angra is a species of Myxophagan beetle in the genus Ytu .
Collocalia is a genus of swifts , containing some of the smaller species termed `` swiftlets '' .
Amphibalanus amphitrite is a species of acorn barnacle in the Balanidae family .
Phyllobius glaucus is a species of weevil found across Europe , especially in carrs .
Aenigmatoceras is a genus of ammonite cephalopod from the Carboniferous of Russia .
Cycloscala is a genus of predatory sea snails , marine prosobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Epitoniidae , commonly known as wentletraps .
Alcithoe davegibbsi is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Volutidae .
Phyllachora banksiae is a species of fungus in the family Phyllachoraceae .
Partula exigua , common name the Moorean viviparous tree snail , was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Erigeron glabellus is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family , called the streamside fleabane .
Luria cinerea , common name , the Atlantic gray cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
It was described by Roesler in 1965 , and contains the species Pararotruda nesiotica .
Osbornodon iamonensis is an extinct species of bone - crushing Hesperocyoninae , a predecessor of modern dogs that were endemic to North America and which lived from the Orellan age of the Early Oligocene to Early Miocene epoch 23.6 - -16.3 Ma and existed for approximately 7.3 million years .
Chaenactis alpigena is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name southern Sierra pincushion .
Lachlathetes is a genus of antlions in the subfamily Palparinae .
Lepidium barnebyanum is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Barneby 's pepperweed , Barneby 's pepper - grass , and Barneby 's ridge - cress .
Dalea foliosa is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name leafy prairie clover .
Ameles spallanzania , common name European dwarf mantis , is a species of praying mantis belonging to the genus Ameles .
Orobanche valida is a species of broomrape known by the common name Rock Creek broomrape .
Mahonia paucijuga is a shrub in the Berberidaceae family described as a species in 1987 .
Helianthus gracilentus is a species of sunflower known by the common name slender sunflower .
The Stejneger 's petrel ( Pterodroma longirostris ) is a species of seabird and a member of the gadfly petrels .
Anthidiellum krombeini is a species of leaf - cutting bee in the genus Anthidiellum , of the family Megachilidae .
Hemipilia silvestrii is an orchid species in the genus Hemipilia .
Xenophonus hirtus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Xenophonus .
Haplochromis riponianus is a species of cichlid found in Lake Victoria and possibly in the adjacent reaches of the Nile .
Acacia enterocarpa , commonly known as jumping jack wattle , is a shrub species that is endemic to eastern Australia .
Plectrohyla thorectes ( Spanish : Rana - de Árbol Moteadais , commonly known as Adler 's mottled tree frog ) a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Eonemachilus longidorsalis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Eonemachilus in which it is currently considered a species inquirenda .
Monoplex keenae is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae family , which includes the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Loxodera is a genus of African plants in the grass family .
Gastornis is an extinct genus of large flightless birds that lived during the late Paleocene and Eocene epochs of the Cenozoic era .
Ranunculus austro - oreganus , the Southern Oregon buttercup , is a plant species endemic to the region around Medford , Oregon .
Tanystropheidae is an extinct family of mostly marine archosauromorph reptiles that lived throughout the Triassic Period .
Oreochromis mweruensis is a species of swamp - dwelling cichlid native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Rwanda and Zambia .
One of the principal host species for Trichopoda pennipes is the southern green stinkbug , Nezara viridula .
Viviparidae , sometimes known as the river snails , are a family of large operculate freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks .
Balaka microcarpa is a species of palm tree .
Oxymeris areolata , common name : the Dark - spotted Auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Thermopsis mollis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Allegheny Mountain goldenbanner , soft bush pea , and soft - haired thermopsis .
Lorandersonia baileyi ( Bailey 's rabbitbrush ) , is a North American species of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Nebria christinae is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Nebriinae family that is endemic to Nepal .
Schiedea kaalae , known as Oahu schiedea or Maʻoliʻoli in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the carnation family , Caryophyllaceae , that is endemic to the island of Oʻahu in Hawaii .
Cladognathus giraffa is a species of beetles belonging to the Lucanidae family .
Allium pskemense is a rare Asian species of wild onion native to Uzbekistan , Kyrgyzstan , and southern Kazakhstan .
Coralliodrilus rugosus is a species of clitellate oligochaete worm , first found in Belize , on the Caribbean side of Central America .
Atriplex cinerea , commonly known as grey saltbush , coast saltbush or barilla , is a plant species in the family Amaranthaceae .
Rhododendron konori , the Konor rhododendron , is a rhododendron species native to Irian Jaya , Indonesia , and Papua New Guinea .
Maytenus crassipes is a species of plant in the Celastraceae family .
The Drosophilidae are a diverse , cosmopolitan family of flies , which includes fruit flies .
Atypichthys is a genus of sea chubs native to inshore waters from Australia to New Zealand and the Kermadec Islands , with currently two recognized species :
Alopecosa pentheri is a wolf spider species in the genus Alopecosa found in Europe ( Bulgaria , Greece ) to Azerbaijan .
The Timor imperial pigeon ( Ducula cineracea ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Lyginia is a genus of three rhizomatous plant species all endemic to South Western Australia .
Planorbis planorbis is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Atopochilus pachychilus is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it occurs in the Lubilonji River in the vicinity of Kanda Kanda .
Conchapelopia is a genus of flies belonging to the family Chironomidae ( the non - biting midges ) .
Woodford 's fruit bat ( Melonycteris woodfordi ) , also known as the orange fruit bat , is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Ecsenius collettei , known commonly as the Collete 's blenny in Papua New Guinea , is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Gluconacetobacter sacchari is a species of acetic acid bacteria first isolated from the leaf sheath of sugar cane and from the pink sugar - cane mealy bug ( Saccharicoccus sacchari ) on sugar cane growing in Queensland and northern New South Wales .
Linum medium , common name stiff yellow flax , is a species of Linum ( flax ) native to eastern North America , as far west as Texas and Wisconsin , east to the Atlantic ocean , and north to Ontario and Maine .
Carabus latreilleanus is a species of beetle in the ground beetle family that is endemic to France .
Aechmea orlandiana is species in the genus Aechmea endemic to Brazil .
Mulsantina picta ( the painted lady beetle or pine lady beetle ) is a species of ladybug belonging to the subfamily Coccinellinae .
Fimbristylis vahlii is a species of sedge known by the common name Vahl 's fimbry .
Sidalcea ranunculacea is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name marsh checkerbloom .
Stiracolpus pagoda , common name the pagoda turret , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turritellidae .
Baikiaea insignis , commonly known as Nkobakoba or Nkoba , is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Conus ebraeus , common name the black - and - white cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Acartauchenius hamulifer is a species of sheet weaver found in Algeria .
Cryptantha incana is a rare species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Tulare cryptantha .
Odontocharacidium aphanes , the green dwarf tetra , is a species of South American darter found in the Amazon River basin .
Veratrum fimbriatum is an uncommon species of false hellebore , a type of plant closely related to the lily .
Elanus is a genus of bird of prey in the elanid kite subfamily .
Geranium californicum is a species of Geranium known by the common name California cranesbill .
Synbranchus is a genus of swamp eels native to Central and South America .
Frasera fastigiata ( syn . Swertia fastigiata ) is a species of flowering plant in the gentian family known by the common name clustered green gentian .
Pythais scutigera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pythais .
Telanthophora is a genus of Mesoamerican plants in the groundsel tribe within the daisy family .
Aleurocanthus woglumi is a species of whitefly in the family Aleyrodidae .
Anodontostoma is a small genus of gizzard shads found in the Indo - Pacific region .
Townsend 's vole ( Microtus townsendii ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae , the sister species of M. canicaudus .
Macrocallista nimbosa , or the sunray venus clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
Thermosinus carboxydivorans is an anaerobic , thermophilic , Gram - negative , carbon - monoxide - oxidizing , hydrogenogenic bacterium , the type species of its genus .
Vomerogobius flavus , the Lemon Goby , is a species of goby native to the marine waters around the Bahamas .
Achyronychia is a monotypic genus of flowering plant containing the single species Achyronychia cooperi , which is known by the common names onyxflower and frost - mat . This plant is native to the Mojave and Sonoran Deserts of northern Mexico and the U.S. states of California , Nevada , Utah and Arizona .
Tosirips is a genus of moths of the tribe Archipini .
Assiminea brevicula , common name the red mangrove snail , is a species of minute operculate snail , a freshwater or marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Assimineidae .
Drymaeus acervatus is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Bulimulidae .
Ephiales cretacea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ephiales .
Sepioloidea pacifica , also known as the Pacific Bobtail Squid , is a species of cuttlefish native to the southern Pacific Ocean ; it occurs off New Zealand in the west and in the Nazca and Sala y Gomez submarine ridges in the east .
Mastax vegeta is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that can be found in such Indian provinces as Darjeeling , Himachal Pradesh , Sikkim and Uttarakhand .
The birch family , the Betulaceae , includes six genera of deciduous nut - bearing trees and shrubs , including the birches , alders , hazels , hornbeams , hazel - hornbeam , and hop - hornbeams numbering about 130 species .
Gliophorus viridis is a species of agaric fungus in the family Hygrophoraceae found in New Zealand .
Trichomorpha esulcata is a species of millipede in the family Chelodesmidae that can be found in San Vito , Costa Rica , where it was found on 17 - -18 April 1972 .
Paracolobus is an extinct genus of primate in the Colobini tribe , which also contains the living colobus monkeys .
Monotes lutambensis is a species of plant in the family Dipterocarpaceae endemic to Tanzania .
Metroxylon sagu ( true sago palm ) is a species of palm in the genus Metroxylon , native to tropical southeastern Asia in Indonesia ( western New Guinea , and the Moluccas ) , Papua New Guinea , Malaysia ( both Peninsular Malaysia and Sarawak ) and possibly also the Philippines ( though may have been introduced there ) .
Rhamphochromis woodi is a species of piscivorous cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers open waters at depths of from 8 to 121 metres ( 26 to 397 ft ) .
Tamarix tetrandra is a species of flowering plant in the family Tamaricaceae , native to south eastern Europe , Turkey , Bulgaria and Crimea .
Monachaster sanderi is a species of sea star in the family Orestieridae .
Cosmochlaina ( from Greek : kosmos = ornament ; xlaina = wrapper / cloak ) is a form genus of nematophyte -- an early ( Silurian -- Devonian ) plant known only from fossil cuticles , often found in association with tubular structures .
Coleochaete is a genus of parenchymatous charophyte green algae in the order Coleochaetales .
Luciobarbus is a genus of ray - finned fishes in the family Cyprinidae .
Leptothrix discophora is one of several species of Leptothrix , known for its sheath , and iron- , manganese- , and recently arsenic - removing properties .
Tergipedidae is a family of sea slugs , aeolid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Fionoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Potentilla grayi is a species of cinquefoil known by the common name Gray 's cinquefoil .
Epialtidae is a family of crabs , containing the subfamilies :
Melanophylla modestei is a species of plant in the Melanophyllaceae family .
Anthosactis pearseae is a species of sea anemone that was discovered in 2007 .
Strongylura marina , known commonly as the Atlantic needlefish , is a common demersal needlefish species common in marinas and other areas with minimal current .
Festuca contracta , commonly known as Tufted Fescue or Land Tussac , is a species of true grass ( Poaceae ) .
Synema globosum is a species of ' crab spiders ' belonging to the family Thomisidae .
Leichardtia is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1849 .
Zelus luridus , also known as the Pale Green Assassin Bug , is a species of assassin bug native to North America .
Cnemaspis heteropholis is a species of gecko found in India ( Gund , Uttara Kannada ) .
Downingia is a genus of 13 annual plants native to western North America and Chile .
Photuris versicolor , is a species complex of firefly common throughout the Eastern United States .
Allium maackii is a species of wild onion native to northeastern Asia ( Heilongjiang , Amur Oblast , Primorye , Khabarovsk , Sakhalin , Kuril Islands ) .
Melanthera tenuifolia ( formerly Lipochaeta tenuifolia ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Waianae Range nehe and slender - leaf nehe .
Drosera capensis , commonly known as the Cape sundew , is a small rosette - forming carnivorous species of perennial sundew native to the Cape in South Africa .
Trifolium ciliolatum is a species of clover known by the common name foothill clover .
Mimulus whitneyi is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Harlequin monkeyflower .
Lithospermum is a genus of plants belonging to the family Boraginaceae .
Draba graminea is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Rocky Mountain draba and San Juan Whitlow - grass .
Acer kenaicum is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a pair of fossil leaves and a samara .
Longitergite is an extinct genus of prawn which existed in Russia during the Lower Miocene period .
Even the higher - level taxonomy is disputed , with some experts preferring to place most lemurs within the infraorder Lemuriformes , while others prefer Lemuriformes to contain all living strepsirrhines , placing all lemurs in superfamily Lemuroidea and all lorises and galagos in superfamily Lorisoidea .
Proteromonadidae is a paraphyletic family of heterokonts , that resemble Opalinidae .
Syngonanthus nitens or golden grass is a grass - like species of Eriocaulaceae which exists in the region of Jalapão , state of Tocantins , Brazil - the region is part of the Brazilian cerrado .
Mucrospirifer is a genus of extinct brachiopod in the class Rhynchonellata ( Articulata ) and the order Spiriferida .
Trinodus , Arthrorhachis and Geragnostus are closely related and it may be appropriate to assign their species to just one genus .
The Forcipomyiinae are a subfamily of biting midges .
Balsamorhiza lanata ( lanate balsamroot ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower tribe within the aster family .
Tinantia anomala , common name false dayflower or widow's - tears , is a plant species in the Commelinaceae , related to the Mexican wandering Jew , Tinantia pringlei .
Deconica coprophila , commonly known as the dung - loving Psilocybe , is a species of mushroom in the Strophariaceae family .
The Polytrichaceae also known as `` Aloe Moss '' is a common family of mosses .
Restrepia teaguei , commonly called the Teague 's Restrepia , is a species of orchid endemic to Ecuador ( Zamora - Chinchipe ) .
Conus platensis is an extinct species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Candida stellata is a species of yeast of the genus Candida .
Papilio lampsacus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in west Java .
Nomascus is the second - most speciose genus of gibbons ( family Hylobatidae ) .
Hibiscus waimeae ( white Kauai rosemallow , Hawaiian : kokiʻo keʻokeʻo , or kokiʻo kea ) is a species of flowering plant in the okra family , Malvaceae , that is endemic to the island of Kauaʻi in Hawaii .
Pteridium aquilinum ( bracken , brake or common bracken ) , also known as `` eagle fern , '' is a species of fern occurring in temperate and subtropical regions in both hemispheres .
Rhynchocinetes is a genus of shrimp , containing the following 14 species :
Onchopristis is a genus of extinct giant sawfish that lived in the Lower Cretaceous to Upper Cretaceous in North Africa and New Zealand .
Huehuecanauhtlus is an extinct genus of hadrosauroid dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous ( Santonian stage ) of Michoacán , western Mexico .
Zaniolepis is a genus of scorpaeniform fish native to the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Phalaenopsis tetraspis is a species of orchid endemic to the Andaman Islands , the Nicobar Islands and northwestern Sumatra .
The Cystofilobasidiaceae are a family of fungi in the order Tremellales .
Callistosporium palmarum is a species of fungus in the Tricholomataceae family , and the type species of the genus Callistosporium .
It contains the single species Diaphoromyrma sofiae , known only from workers from the type locality in Bahia , Brazil .
Cosmochilus is genus of cyprinid fish found in East and Southeast Asia .
Bothrogonia is a genus of leafhopper with a large number of species distributed across the Old World .
Valvata bicarinata , common name the two - ridge valvata , is a species of small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Valvatidae , the valve snails .
Canthigaster rapaensis is a species of fish in the Tetraodontidae family .
Pulcratis reticulatus is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Pulcratis .
Krascheninnikovia ceratoides ( Pamirian winterfat ) is a plant species native to central and southern Europe , northern Africa , and parts of Asia .
Hemitaeniochromis brachyrhynchus is a species of fish in the family Cichlidae .
The Bocaina tree frog , Aplastodiscus callipygius , or perereca - verde , is a species of frog in the family Hylidae , endemic to Brazil .
Longidorus is a genus of needle nematode .
Priochirus is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Staphylinidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Bulbithecium hyalosporum .
Apolemichthys xanthotis , common names Yellow - ear angelfish and Red Sea angelfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Pomacanthidae .

Dysoneura zherikhini is a species of insect in the genus Dysoneura .

Nerita umlaasiana is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae .
Merrilliobryum is a genus of moss in family Myriniaceae .
Diplacodes melanopsis is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae known commonly as the blackfaced percher or black - faced percher .
Cynarctoides roii is an extinct species of Cynarctoides , belonging to the subfamily Borophaginae and tribe Phlaocyonini , a canid which inhabited west central North America from the Late Oligocene to Miocene living 30.8 - -20.6 mya and existed for approximately 10.2 million years .
Cyclothone is a genus of bioluminescent bristlemouths which typically grow to around 3 inches ( though some species are known to be larger ) .
Gymnocalycium quehlianum ( Quehla chin cactus ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cactaceae , native to northern Argentina .
Herichthys teporatus , also known as the Soto la Marina cichlid , is a species of cichlid fish endemic to Mexico where it occurs in the Soto la Marina drainage in the state of Tamaulipas .
Renanthera coccinea is a species of orchid occurring from Hainan to Indochina .
Carex archeri , known as Archer 's sedge , is a species of sedge in the genus Carex , endemic to south - eastern Australia .
The Cetomimiformes or whalefishes are an order of small , deep - sea ray - finned fish .
Mitella ovalis is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common names coastal miterwort and oval - leaf miterwort .
Saxifraga stellaris , the starry saxifrage or hairy kidney - wort , is an Arctic -- alpine species of saxifrage .
Bolinus cornutus , or horned murex , is a predatory species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex or rock snails .
Rhinophis oxyrhynchus , commonly known as Schneider 's earth snake , is a species of uropeltid snake endemic to Sri Lanka .
Hawaiia minuscula , common name the minute gem or minute gem snail , is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pristilomatidae .
Zhenbaspis is an extinct genus ptychopariid trilobite .
Plagiochasma intermedium is a liverwort species in the genus Plagiochasma found in China .
Hippa adactyla is a species of small , sand - burrowing decapod crustacean found living along the coasts of Indo - West Pacific waters .
Nautilus belauensis , also known as the Palau nautilus , is a species of nautilus native to the waters around the Pacific island nation of Palau .
Gaura coccinea is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by several common names , including scarlet beeblossom , scarlet gaura , and linda tarde .
Pratulum pulchellum is a species of cockle , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Cardiidae .
The currently recognised species in this genus is Fenestraria rhopalophylla .
Allobates myersi ( common name : Myers ' poison frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family found in Amazonian Colombia , likely also in adjacent Brazil and northeastern Peru .
Anomobryum julaceum , the slender silver - moss , is a species of bryophyte native to all continents except South America and Antarctica .
Chalcosyrphus valgus is a medium - sized species of hoverfly with a widespread range throughout the palearctic region .
Foch 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys fochi ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Veronica anagallis - aquatica is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names water speedwell , blue water - speedwell , and brook pimpernel .
Hampala salweenensis is a southeast Asian species of cyprinid , endemic to the basin of the Salween .
Cerion nanus is a species of medium - sized air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod in the family Cerionidae , which are sometimes known as the peanut snails .
Labidochromis strigatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known to occur in areas with rocky substrates around Likoma Island and Chisumulu Island .
Mittermeier 's mouse lemur ( Microcebus mittermeieri ) is a species of mouse lemur known only from Anjanaharibe - Sud Special Reserve in Madagascar .
Castilleja christii is a rare species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common name Christ 's Indian paintbrush .
Eleutherodactylus dimidiatus is a rare species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Cuba .
Dichanthelium lanuginosum ( Panic grass ) is a species of grass .
Penstemon pudicus is a rare species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names bashful beardtongue and Kawich Range beardtongue .
Philine powelli is a species of sea snail , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Philinidae , the headshield slugs .
Calciphilopteris is a genus of ferns in the family Pteridaceae .
Dsungaripterus was a genus of pterosaur , with an average wingspan of 3 metres ( 9.8 ft ) .
Thalattosauroidea is a superfamily of thalattosaurs , a Triassic group of marine reptiles .
The Phalangeroidea are a superfamily of mammals that include the families Burramyidae and Phalangeridae , as well as the extinct families Ektopodontidae and Miralinidae .
Quercus daimingshanensis is a rare Asian species of trees in the beech family .
Ephedrophila lucasi is a species of snout moth in the genus Ephedrophila .
Nebria angusticollis is a species of ground beetle in Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in the Alps of France , Italy , and Switzerland .
Pyozia is an extinct genus of basal Middle Permian varanopid synapsid known from Russia .
Epitamyra minusculalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Epitamyra .
Metaporana obtusa is a species of plant in the Convolvulaceae family endemic to Yemen .
Pagodula aculeata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod in the family Muricidae .
Ramallichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the lower Cenomanian .
Barringtonia calyptrata is a species of mangrove belonging to the family Lecythidaceae .
Cetonurichthys subinflatus , the smallpore whiptail , is a species of rattail found in the Indian Ocean waters near Australia .
Cordicephalus gracilis is the only species in the extinct genus Cordicephalus , a genus of prehistoric frogs .
Eviota sigillata , commonly called seven - figure pygmy goby or adorned dwarfgoby , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiidae .
The Lichinales are an order of ascomycete fungi .
Oliva reticulata , common name the blood olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Rhabdotis aulica , known as the emerald fruit chafer , is a species of Scarabaeidae , the dung beetle family , and is found in Africa .
Gomphocerinae is a subfamily of grasshoppers , commonly called slant - faced grasshoppers .
Anisopodus costaricensis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Lara & Shenefelt in 1964 .
Lejopyge laevigata is a species of agnostid trilobite belonging to the genus Lejopyge .
Dracula chestertonii , commonly known as the Frog 's Skin , is a species of orchid endemic to Colombia .
Astrangia poculata , the northern star coral or northern cup coral , is a species of non - reefbuilding stony coral in the family Rhizangiidae .
Talaridris is a genus of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Talaridris mandibularis .
Shortia galacifolia has also been reported in Japan , as have three other species of Shortia .
Economidichthys pygmaeus , the Western Greece goby , is a species of freshwater goby endemic to western Greece where it is an inhabitant of streams and rivers .
Festuca arvernensis ( also known as Field fescue ) is a species of perennial plant from Poaceae family .
Streptomyces cuspidosporus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Kyoto in Japan .
Aloinopsis malherbei is a species of succulent plant , also known as the `` Giant Jewel plant '' .
Pecteilis radiata ( syn . Habenaria radiata ) is a species of orchid found in China , Japan , Korea and Russia .
The Acidobacteriaceae are a family of Acidobacteria .
The Boletaceae are a family of mushrooms , primarily characterized by developing their spores in small pores on the underside of the mushroom , instead of gills , as are found in agarics .
Oncorhynchus rastrosus ( synonym Smilodonichthys rastrosus ) also known as the sabertooth salmon , is an extinct species of salmon that lived along the Pacific coast of North America , first appearing in the late Miocene of California , then dying out some time during the Pleistocene .
Phaius is a genus of large , mostly terrestrial orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) .
Heniochus is a genus of butterflyfishes native to the Indo - Pacific .
Pennahia anea , commonly known as the bigeye croaker , is a species of fish native to the Indian region .
Carabus dufouri dufouri is a subspecies of black coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found on Gibraltar and in Spain .
Illadopsis ( from illas , Greek for thrush and opsis , appearing ) is a genus of secretive forest birds in the Pellorneidae family .
Candalides geminus , the Geminus Blue , is a species of butterfly of the Lycaenidae family .
Amesiella philippinensis is a species of orchid endemic to the Island of Luzon in the Philippines .
Acanthobrama telavivensis , commonly known as the Yarkon bream or Yarkon bleak , is a species of freshwater ray - finned fish of the Cyprinidae family found only in Israel , in the Yarkon River system .
Margarites keepi , common name the Keep margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Helenium vernale is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Savanna sneezeweed or spring sneezeweed .
Camponotus monju is a species of carpenter ant known from Japan and Taiwan .
The Fagales are an order of flowering plants , including some of the best - known trees .
Daxata is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , containing the following species : subgenus Daxata Daxata camelus Pascoe , 1864 subgenus Laodaxata Daxata lepesmei Breuning , 1961 subgenus Taxada Daxata anterufipennis Breuning , 1961 Daxata confusa Pascoe , 1869 Daxata laosensis Breuning , 1938 Daxata sumatrensis Breuning , 1961 Daxata ustulata Pascoe , 1866
Blepharocerus rubescens is a species of snout moth in the genus Blepharocerus .
Ypsilopus is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae native to Africa .
The Anarthriaceae are a family of three genera , Anarthria , Hopkinsia and Lyginia of flowering plants .
Oxycarpha is a genus of Colombian flowering plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Phyllodesmium jakobsenae is a species of sea slug , an aolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Facelinidae .
Stenamma andersoni is a Neotropical species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Penicillium concentricum is a coprophilic , anamorph fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces roquefortine C and patulin .
Campestigma is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1912 .
Kyllinga brevifolia is a species of sedge known by several common names , including shortleaf spikesedge , green kyllinga , and perennial greenhead sedge .
Angela armata is a species of praying mantis from the Mantidae family and Angela genus .
Acmella pusilla ( dwarf spotflower ) is a species of flowering herb in the sunflower family .
Microphestia animalcula is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Microphestia .
Zygodontomys is a genus of rodent in the tribe Oryzomyini of the family Cricetidae .
Leiostyla corneocostata is a species of land snail in the family Lauriidae known commonly as the Madeiran land snail .
Donacoceras is an extinct genus of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod , essentially a Nautiloid that lived in what would be North America during the Ordovician from 460.5 - -443.7 mya , existing for approximately 16.8 million years .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Stalpersia orientalis .
Strophurus is a genus of lizards in the family Gekkonidae .
Poa kerguelensis is a species of tussock grass native to various subantarctic islands .
Ophisops beddomei , commonly known as Beddome 's snake - eye , is a species of lizard endemic to the Western Ghats of India .
The Madeiran wood pigeon ( Columba palumbus maderensis ) was a subspecies of the wood pigeon ( Columba palumbus ) endemic to Madeira ( Portugal ) , and found in the island 's Laurel forest habitat .
Micrixalus herrei is a newly redescribed species of frog in the Micrixalidae family .
Zosterops is a genus of birds containing the typical white - eyes .
Perenniporia podocarpi is a species of resupinate ( encrusting ) polypore .
Neoheterophrictus uttarakannada is a species of Neoheterophrictus .
Vaccinium elliottii ( Elliott 's blueberry ) is a species of Vaccinium in the blueberry group ( Vaccinium sect . Cyanococcus ) .
Lambeosaurus ( /ˌlæmbioʊˈsɔːrəs/ LAM - bee - o - SAWR - əs ; meaning `` Lambe 's lizard '' ) is a genus of hadrosaurid dinosaur that lived about 76 to 75 million years ago , in the Late Cretaceous period ( Campanian ) of North America .
The family Archeocrypticidae is a small group of beetles with no vernacular common name , though recent authors have coined the name cryptic fungus beetles .
Betta tussyae is a species of gourami endemic to Malaysia where it is only known from Pahang .
Mortoniceras is an ammonoid genus belonging to the superfamily Acanthocerataceae , named by Meek in 1876 , based on Ammonites vespertinu , named by Morton in 1834 .
Capitocrassus castaneus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Capitocrassus .
Hyacinthoides lingulata is a species of bulbous plant that lives in North Africa , from Morocco to Tunisia .
Also known as the Siskiyou caddisfly , Neothremma siskiyou is a species of insect found in the state of California .
Conocramboides seychellellus seychellellus from Seychelles Conocramboides seychellellus emmerezellus ( de Joannis , 1915 ) from La Réunion and Mauritius Foodplants of the larvae of this species are Poaceae ( Cynodon dactylon , Axonopus compressus , Digitaria didactyla , Zoysia matrella and Cynodon dactylon )
Platyallabes tihoni is the only species in the genus Platyallabes of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Clariidae .
Mimoceroplesis coussementi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimoceroplesis .
Artemisia biennis is a species of sagebrush known by the common name ' biennial wormwood .
Xylaria hypoxylon is a species of fungus in the genus Xylaria .
Willisornis is a genus of birds in the family Thamnophilidae .
Pseudogygites is an extinct genus of the class Trilobita from the Middle and Upper Ordovician .
Mycena flavescens is a species of Mycenaceae fungus .
Nothocalais alpestris is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name alpine lake false dandelion .
Yucca × schottii is a plant species in the genus Yucca , native to southern Arizona , southwestern New Mexico , and the northern parts of Sonora and Chihuahua ..
Caesalpinia mexicana is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae .
Nebria tatrica fatrensis is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the mountain range of Velká Fatra in Slovakia , and Czech Republic .
Dioscoreophyllum gossweileri is a plant species native to Angola .
Penicillium brevistipitatum is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from the Jilin Province in China .
Campephilus is a genus of large American woodpeckers in the family Picidae .
Cornuchariesthes albomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cornuchariesthes .
Russellosaurus is an extinct genus of tethysaurine mosasauroid from the Late Cretaceous of North America .
Pachydactylus tetensis , commonly known as the Tete thick - toed gecko or Zambezi thick - toed gecko , is a species of gecko endemic to East Africa .
Crepis phoenix , is a Chinese species of plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Disocactus phyllanthoides , the nopalxochitl or German empress , is a species of flowering plant in the cactus family Cactaceae and is commonly grown as an ornamental houseplant .
Ambulycini is a tribe of moths of the Sphingidae family .
Actophilornis is a genus of jacana .
Juncus confusus is a species of rush known by the common name Colorado rush .
Miridus quadrivirgatus is a species of plant bug belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Mirinae .
Perissoza scripta is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Perissoza of the family Ulidiidae .
It contains only one species , Caridarctia albicancellata , which can be found in Argentina .
Ichthyostega ( Greek : `` fish roof '' ) is an early tetrapod genus that lived at the end of the Upper Devonian period .
Suksdorfia ranunculifolia is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name buttercup suksdorfia .
Hellinsia tariensis is a species of moth in the genus Hellinsia , known from Papua New Guinea .
Festuca porcii is a species of grass which can be found in Central , Eastern , and southeastern parts of Europe .
Manilkara bidentata is a species of Manilkara native to a large area of northern South America , Central America and the Caribbean .
Nebria davatchii is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Iran .
Leucoagaricus rubrotinctus is a widespread species of fungus in the family Agaricaceae .
Ovalipes is a genus of crabs in the family Polybiidae , containing 11 extant species :
Carbactinoceratidae is a family of extinct cephalopods with external shells that lived around 325 million years ago , during the Carboniferous period .
Caprichromis is a small genus of haplochromine cichlids endemic to Lake Malawi in East Africa .
Cayratia debilis is a species of plant native to equatorial Africa .
Plectorhinchus diagrammus , the striped sweetlips , is a species of grunt native to the western Pacific Ocean where it is a denizen of coral reefs .
Chromolaena frustrata called Cape Sable false thoroughwort , or Cape Sable thoroughwort , is a rare North American species of flowering shrub in the sunflower family .
Brickellia amplexicaulis ( earleaf brickellbush ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Penicillium canis is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from a dog which suffered from osteomyelitis .
Palafoxia riograndensis , the Rio Grande palafox or Rio Grande Spanish needles , is a plant species native to Texas , Chihuahua and Coahuila .
Colchicum parlatoris is a small species native to Greece .
The Pangani longclaw ( Macronyx aurantiigula ) is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family , which includes the pipits and wagtails .
Polypogon maritimus is a species of grass known by the common names Mediterranean beard grass and Mediterranean rabbitsfoot grass .
Pyrgomantis nasuta is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Cape Province , Cameroon , Kenya , Natal , Namibia , Somalia , and Tanzania .
Odettea laosensis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Odettea .
Lasthenia chrysantha is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name alkalisink goldfields .
Carex pauciflora , known as few - flowered sedge , is a perennial species of sedge in the family Cyperaceae native to Holarctic wetlands .
Clausena lansium , also known as wampee ( Clausena wampi ) , is a species of strongly scented evergreen trees 3 - -8 m tall , in the family Rutaceae , native to southeast Asia .
Hepatozoon is a genus of Apicomplexan protozoa which incorporates over 300 species obligate intraerythrocytic parasites .
Cochlefelis is a genus of sea catfishes found in coastal and freshwaters from Southeast Asia to Australia .
Trypanosoma lewisi is a parasite of Rattus species and other rodents such as mice and kangaroo rats in America .
Aulacocerida is an order of primitive coleoid cephalopods , possibly derived from michelinoceraitids ( Orthocerida ) early in the Devonian , which in turn gave rise to the Belemnites .
Megaspora is a genus of lichens in the family Megasporaceae .
The Mendoza tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys mendocinus ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Erigeron bonariensis is a species of Erigeron , found throughout the tropics and subtropics as a pioneer plant ; its precise native origin is unknown , but most likely Central America or South America .
Formica rufa , also known as the red wood ant , southern wood ant or horse ant , is a boreal member of the Formica rufa group of ants , and is the type species for that group .
It is the only species of the genus Cirroteuthis .
Ipomopsis tenuituba is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name slendertube skyrocket , or slendertube ipomopsis .
Calyx shackletoni is a species of demosponge first found on the coast of South Georgia island , in the south west Southern Ocean .
Calochortus ciscoensis is a North American species of flowering plants in the lily family first described for modern science in 2008 .
Phalloptychus is a genus of poeciliids native to eastern and southern Brazil , northern Argentina , Paraguay and Uruguay .
Cleistochloa is a genus of grasses native to Australia and New Guinea .
Chondrina tatrica is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Chondrinidae .
Chytriomyces elegans is a species of fungus in the genus Chytriomyces .
Anisopodus andicola is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Kirsch in 1889 .
Johora thaiana is a species of freshwater crab described from specimens found in Thailand , as the name was derived .
Attelabus auratus is a species of leaf and bud weevils belonging to the family Attelabidae .
Lepeophtheirus is a genus of sea lice .
Cargninia is an extinct genus of basal lepidosaur from the Late Triassic period .
Stenocoptoides ciliatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Stenocoptoides .
Gilia sinuata is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name rosy gilia .
Periclimenes pholeter , is a species of shrimp belonging to the family Palaemonidae .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Pseudopleospora ruthenica .
Galium aschenbornii is a species of flowering plant in the genus Galium , native to Mexico , Central America , Colombia and Ecuador .
Aphelia alleniana , the wide - striped leafroller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Kazachstania exigua is a yeast species that commonly occurs in olive brine and in some kefir cultures .
Lawrencia is a plant genus in the family Malvaceae .
Baptornis ( `` diving bird '' ) is a genus of flightless aquatic birds from the Late Cretaceous , some 87 - 80 million years ago ( roughly mid - Coniacian to mid - Campanian faunal stages ) .
Anchitherium was a browsing ( leaf eating ) horse that originated in the early Miocene of North America and subsequently dispersed to Europe and Asia , where it gave rise to the larger bodied genus Sinohippus .
Lagophylla minor is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family known by the common name lesser hareleaf .
Alectryon subcinereus , commonly named Native Quince , Wild Quince or Bird 's Eye , is a species of shrubs or small trees , constituting part of the plant family Sapindaceae .
Ficus fergusonii , is a species of plant in the fig genus , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Melathemma polita is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Melathemma .
The only known species of this genus is Urojana eborea , which is known from Ivory Coast .
Amphisbaena ridleyi , known by the common names Ridley 's worm lizard or the Noronha worm lizard , is a species of amphisbaenian in the genus Amphisbaena .
The annelids ( Annelida , from Latin anellus , `` little ring '' ) , also known as the ringed worms or segmented worms , are a large phylum , with over 17,000 extant species including ragworms , earthworms , and leeches .
Bacillus firmus is a species of bacteria within the genus Bacillus .
Polistes snelleni , the Japanese paper wasp , is a common social wasp species in central and northern Japan .
Obtortionidae is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Cerithioidea , that is within the clade Cerithimorpha or in clade Sorbeoconcha .
Toxicodendron rydbergii the western poison ivy , is a species of Toxicodendron in the cashew family .
Chromolaena ivifolia called ivy - leaf false thoroughwort , or ivyleaf thoroughwort , is an American species of flowering shrub in the sunflower family .
Psiloceratidae is an extinct family of cephalopods belonging to the ammonite subclass .
The Mekong wagtail ( Motacilla samveasnae ) is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Enkianthus perulatus ( dodan - tsutsuji ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Ericaceae , native to Japan .
Culex is a genus of mosquitoes , several species of which serve as vectors of one or more important diseases of birds , humans and other animals .
Callionymus cooperi , Cooper 's dragonet , is a species of dragonet found only around the Maldives where it occurs at depths of from 73 to 81 metres ( 240 to 266 ft ) .
Megacephala whelani is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sumlin in 1992 , and is native to Australia .
The Javan mossy tree frog ( Litoria javana ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Cheiracanthium gratum is a spider species found in Germany and Hungary .
The Bradyrhizobiaceae are a family of bacteria , with ten genera .
Arctostaphylos auriculata ( Mount Diablo Manzanita ) is an endangered species of Arctostaphylos endemic to California , and limited in geography to the area surrounding Mount Diablo , in Contra Costa County .
The superfamily Limacinoidea is a taxonomic group of small floating sea snails , pelagic marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks .
Dalbergia nigra , commonly known as the Bahia rosewood , jacarandá da Bahia , Brazilian rosewood , Rio rosewood , jacarandá de Brasil , pianowood , caviuna , or obuina , is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Radfordia palustris is a species of mite in the subgenus Hesperomyobia of the genus Radfordia .
The type species is Siamodon nimngami .
Cheirothyris is a genus of fossil brachiopod from the Upper Jurassic period .
Coralliozetus boehlkei , the Barcheek blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found from the Gulf of California to Costa Rica , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Protomelas similis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it prefers shallow waters with plentiful vegetation .
Tetrastes is a genus of birds in the grouse subfamily .
Peronospora conglomerata is a biotrophic plant pathogen ( part of the downy mildew taxon ) which affects geranium species .
Planctoteuthis is a genus of chiroteuthid squid comprising five species , occurring worldwide in lower mesopelagic to bathypelagic depths in tropical to temperate waters .
Lessingia arachnoidea is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Crystal Springs lessingia .
The Telmatobiinae , water frogs , are a subfamily of frogs endemic to South America .
Pachycephala is a genus of birds native to Oceania and Southeast Asia .
The Dalceridae are a small family of moths with 84 known species mostly found in the Neotropical region with a few reaching the far south of the Nearctic region .
It contains the single species Dotha ctenuchoides , which is found in Sumatra .
The Sichuan leaf warbler ( Phylloscopus forresti ) is a species of leaf warbler found only in China .
Glyptostrobus pensilis , also known as Chinese swamp cypress , is the sole living species in the genus Glyptostrobus .
Haworthia venosa is a species of flowering plant in the genus Haworthia belonging to the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , native to Namibia and South Africa .
Zholsuchus is a genus of crocodyliform that may have been a goniopholidid mesoeucrocodylian , but is only known from scanty material ( a right premaxilla , one of the bones of the tip of the snout ) .
Hippichthys is a genus of pipefishes native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans and the landmasses around them .
Olallamys is a genus of Andean soft - furred spiny rat that range from Panama through Colombia and Venezuela to northern Ecuador .
Nasutitermes triodiae is a grass - eating species of snouted harvester termite that occurs in the Northern Territory of Australia .

Pachymerium tabacarui is a species of centipede in Geophilidae family that is endemic to Romania .
Archosauromorpha ( Greek for `` ruling lizard forms '' ) is an infraclass of diapsid reptiles that first appeared during the late Permian and became more common during the Triassic .
Chrysomyza anaglypha is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Chrysomyza of the family Ulidiidae .
Sanicula crassicaulis is a species of flowering plant in the parsley family known by the common names Pacific blacksnakeroot and Pacific sanicle .

Acanthacaris is a genus of deep - water lobsters .

Tetracarpaea has one species , Tetracarpaea tasmannica , an evergreen , bushy shrub from subalpine areas of Tasmania .
The japygids ( family Japygidae ) are a taxon of hexapods , of the order Diplura .
Fimbristylis is a genus of sedges .
Paris quadrifolia , the herb - paris or true lover 's knot , is a Eurasian species of the genus Paris in the family Melanthiaceae , although authorities formerly regarded it as part of the Liliaceae family .

Recilia obongsanensis is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that is endemic to Korea .
Stagmatoptera reimoseri is a species of praying mantis in the genus Stagmatoptera .
The family Cranchiidae comprises the approximately 60 species of glass squid , also known as cockatoo squid , cranchiid , cranch squid , or bathyscaphoid squid .
It contains only one species , Eratophyes amasiella , which is found in Asia Minor , the Netherlands , Germany , Denmark and Sweden .
Stanleya viridiflora is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names green princesplume and green - flowered prince 's plume .
Trichogypsia is a genus of calcareous sponges belonging to the family Grantiidae .

Haemanthus is a Southern African genus of flowering plants in the family Amaryllidaceae , subfamily Amaryllidoideae .
The Big Mouth Cave salamander ( Gyrinophilus palleucus necturoides ) , a lungless salamander , is a subspecies of the Tennessee cave salamander ( Gyrinophilus palleucus ) .
Vilchesia valenciai is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Vilchesia .
Podistera is a genus of flowering plants in the carrot family .
Anatoma philippinica is a species of a minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Anatomidae .
The Arabian leopard ( Panthera pardus nimr ) is a leopard subspecies native to the Arabian Peninsula and classified as Critically Endangered by IUCN since 1996 .
Ribes marshallii is a North American species of currant known by the common names Hupa gooseberry and Marshall 's gooseberry .
Pleuroflammula is a genus of fungi in the Crepidotaceae family .
Rhyothemis graphiptera , known as the graphic flutterer or banded flutterer , is a species of dragonfly of the family Libellulidae .
