Macroperipatus insularis is a species of invertebrate in the Peripatidae family .
Centruroides exilicauda , the Baja California bark scorpion , is a species of bark scorpion found in Baja California .
Nabalus crepidineus ( formerly Prenanthes crepidinea ) , commonly called the nodding rattlesnakeroot , is a species of plant in the Asteraceae family occurring in the northern central United States .
Polypodiodes formosana ( 台湾水龙骨 ) is a species of ferns in the Polypodiaceae family endemic to Fujian and Taiwan .
Glyptothorax kurdistanicus is a species of sisorid catfish .
Condica aroana is a species of Noctuidae that occurs in Australia and Borneo .
Capitanopsis is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1916 .
Amphipholis squamata , common names brooding snake star and dwarf brittle star , is a species of brittle star in the family Amphiuridae .
Thoburnia hamiltoni ( rustyside sucker ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Catostomidae family .
Kallirhynchia is an extinct genus of brachiopod found in Jurassic strata in Europe , North Africa , the Middle East , India and Uzbekistan .
Palmatorappia solomonis , or Solomon Island palm frog , is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Hypericum asplundii is a species of flowering plant in the family Hypericaceae .
Pseudochalcothea virens is a species of beetles belonging to the Scarabaeidae family , Cetoniinae subfamily .
Thomashuxleya is an extinct genus of notoungulate mammal , named after famous 19th - century biologist Thomas Huxley .
Cenchrus echinatus is a species of grass known by the common names southern sandbur , spiny sandbur , southern sandspur , and in Australia , Mossman River grass .
Acacia flexifolia , commonly known as bent - leaf wattle , is a shrub species that is endemic to eastern Australia .
Cibotium schiedei , common name Mexican tree fern , is a species of tree fern , of the genus Cibotium .
Ephedra przewalskii is a species of Ephedra that is native to Central Asia , Mongolia , Pakistan , and parts of China ( Gansu , Inner Mongolia , Ningxia , Qinghai , and Tibet ) .
Gamochaeta pensylvanica , called Pennsylvania cudweed or Pennsylvania everlasting , is a widespread species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Acragas carinatus is a species of jumping spider in the genus Acragas ( genus ) .
Hypselognathus is a genus of pipefishes endemic to Australia where they are only known from the southern coast .
Fusinus ocelliferus , common name the long - siphoned whelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Platypleura sylvia is a species of cicada endemic to South Africa .
The Bicolored Trailing Ant , ( Monomorium floricola ) , is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Ranunculus pedatifidus is a species of buttercup known by the common names surefoot buttercup , northern buttercup , and birdfoot buttercup .
Eryngium cuneifolium is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names wedgeleaf eryngo , wedge - leaved button - snakeroot , and simply snakeroot .
Rubus alpinus is a New World species of brambles in the rose family .
Philothamnus semivariegatus , commonly known as the spotted bush snake , is a species of non - venomous colubrid snake , endemic to Africa .
Osteolepis ( ' bone scale ' ) is an extinct genus of lobe - finned fish from the Devonian period .
Maasella edwardsi is a species of soft coral in the family Paralcyoniidae .
The Rhyacophilidae are a family in the insect order of Trichoptera .
The Colima pygmy owl ( Glaucidium palmarum ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
The Anaxyelidae are a wood wasp family within the Symphyta , containing only a single living species , Syntexis libocedrii , ( also called the cedar wood wasp or incense - cedar wood wasp ) , though the family has an extensive Mesozoic fossil record ; this species is thus a `` living fossil '' .
Neolaeops microphthalmus , the crosseyed flounder , is a deep water species of lefteye flounder found in the Indian and Western Pacific Oceans .
Neusticomys is a genus of semiaquatic South American rodents in the family Cricetidae .
Carabus galicianus is a species of beetle from Carabidae family that can be found in Spain and Portugal .
The family Neanuridae contains pudgy short - legged springtails of the order Poduromorpha .
Lachesilla bernardi is a species of Psocoptera from Lachesillidae family that can be found in Austria , Croatia , Cyprus , France , Greece , Hungary , Italy , Poland , Portugal , Romania , Spain , and Switzerland .
The WWF held a competition to name the butterfly , and the species was named after the winner Isobel Talks ( being named Pronophila isobelae ) .
Ansonia spinulifer , also known as spiny slender toad or Kina Balu stream toad , is a species of true toad in the family Bufonidae .
Ichthyapus keramanus is a species of snake eel native to the western Pacific Ocean where it is only known to occur around the Kerama Islands near Okinawa , Japan .
Echiniscus testudo ( also known as Turtle Water Bear ) is a species of tardigrade native to China , Greenland , and Mongolia as well as Europe , the Middle East and North Africa .
Euphorbia parishii is a species of euphorb known by the common name Parish 's sandmat .
There are two extinct species in the genus , Kuphus incrassatus and Kuphus fistula .
Cerastium brachypetalum , commonly called gray chickweed , grey mouse - ear or gray mouse - ear chickweed , is a spring blooming annual plant species .
Lacuna parva , common name the tiny lacuna , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Actinella fausta is a species of land snail in the family Hygromiidae .
Dentarene sarcina , common name the spiny wheel shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Astragalus mulfordiae is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Mulford 's milkvetch .
Morchellium argus , the red - flake ascidian , is a species of colonial sea squirt , a tunicate in the family Polyclinidae .
The Mexican woodnymph ( Thalurania ridgwayi ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family and is endemic to western Mexico .
Euonymus japonicus ( evergreen spindle or Japanese spindle ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Celastraceae , native to Japan , Korea and China .
Disteira major , commonly known as the olive - headed sea snake or the greater sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Murexsul mariae is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a predatory marine gastropod mollusc in the Family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Acropora lovelli is a species of acroporid coral found in the northern Indian Ocean , the central Indo - Pacific , Australia and the oceanic west Pacific Ocean .
The Tonkean black macaque or Tonkean macaque ( Macaca tonkeana ) is a species of primate in the family Cercopithecidae .
Daviesia leptophylla , commonly known as Narrow - leaf Bitter - pea , is a broom - like shrub species in the family Fabaceae .
Puntius snyderi ( common name : Snyder 's barb ) is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Taiwan .
Octomeria concolor is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Rio de Janeiro , Paraná ) .
Oligoryzomys magellanicus , also known as the Patagonian colilargo and the Magellanic pygmy rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oligoryzomys of the family Cricetidae .
Coronilla minima is a species of flowering plant from the Fabaceae family that can be found in Eastern and Central Spain .
Septalites is a genus of cornulitid tubeworms .
Petitella georgiae , the false rummynose tetra , is a species of characin found in Amazon Basin in Brazil and Peru .
Catocala amica , the girlfriend underwing , is an Erebidae species .
Ulva clathrata is a species of seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found in such European countries as Azores , Belgium , Ireland , Netherlands , and the United Kingdom .
Drosera intricata is a scrambling or climbing perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Abutilon palmeri , with the common names Palmer 's Abutilon , Superstition Mallow , and Palmer 's Indian Mallow , ) is a species of Abutilon native the Southwestern United States and Northwestern Mexico .
Phyllostachys bambusoides , commonly called madake , giant timber bamboo or Japanese timber bamboo , is a bamboo species in the genus Phyllostachys .
Barreirosuchus is an extinct genus of trematochampsid notosuchian known from the Late Cretaceous of São Paulo State , southeastern Brazil .
Nepenthes ventricosa ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz vɛntrɪˈkoʊzə/ ; from New Latin : ventricosus = having a swelling on one side ) is a tropical pitcher plant endemic to the Philippines , where it is a highland species , growing at an elevation of 1,000 - -2,000 metres ( 3,300 - -6,600 ft ) above sea level .
Aspidistra campanulata is a species of flowering plant .
Mordellistena cypria is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae and in the Mordellistena genus .
Helice tridens is a species of crab which lives on mudflats around the coasts of Japan and the Korean Peninsula .
Gyrodactylus is a genus of ectoparasites .
Renea bourguignatiana is a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Aciculidae .
Sidalcea glaucescens is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name waxy checkerbloom .
Ophiocara is a genus of sleeper gobies native to tropical waters of the western Pacific Ocean and in fresh waters along the coast of Madagascar .
Entomocorus radiosus is a species of driftwood catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Rio Paraguay in the pantanal region of Mato Grosso .
Phacelia cronquistiana , Cronquist 's phacelia , is a plant species native to Utah and Arizona , known only from Kane and Mohave Counties .
Argyrotaenia mariana , the gray - banded leafroller moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Rhaphiodon echinus is a species of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , endemic to eastern Brazil .
Inape biremis is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family which is endemic to Colombia where it can be found on Nevado del Tolima .
Megalaemyia costalis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Megalaemyia of the family Tephritidae .
Stevia plummerae , Plummer 's candyleaf , is a plant species known from Arizona , New Mexico , Chihuahua , Sonora and Durango It is an herb up to 80 cm tall , with white , pink or red flowers .
Hibbertia obtusifolia , commonly known as Hoary Guinea - flower , is a small shrub species that is native to south - eastern Australia .
Pelorocephalus ( meaning `` monstrous head '' in Greek ) is an extinct genus of chigutisaurid temnospondyls from Late Triassic of Argentina .
Setohyllisia setosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Setohyllisia .
Variraptor ( /ˈværɨræptər/ VARR - i - rap - tor ; `` Var thief '' ) is a genus of coelurosaurian theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of France .
Penicillium cartierense is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which is named after Cartierheide in the Netherlands where this species was first found .
It consists of only one species Palaeopsyche melanias , which is found in the wet tropics of Queensland .
Achnopogon is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1957 .
The Sunda forktail ( Enicurus velatus ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Carcharodon hubbelli is an extinct species of shark known from fossils found in the Pisco Formation in south - west Peru .
Vibrio campbellii is a Gram - negative , curved rod - shaped , marine bacterium closely related to its sister species , Vibrio harveyi .
Gonatodus is an extinct genus of palaeonisciform fish that lived during the Tournaisian stage of the Mississippian epoch .
Eriogonum maculatum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name spotted buckwheat .
Polyalthia hirtifolia is a species of plant in the family Annonaceae .
Jamesianthus is a genus of North American flowering plants in the daisy family .
Rubus prestonensis a rare North American species of brambles in the rose family .
Alopecosa solitaria is a wolf spider species in the genus Alopecosa found in Europe and Russia .
The genus Planigale are small carnivorous marsupials found in Australia and New Guinea .
Urena is a genus of plants which grow in various tropical and subtropical areas throughout the world .
Sepia papillata is a species of cuttlefish native to the southeastern Atlantic Ocean and southwestern Indian Ocean .
Acanthonautilus is an extinct genus in the nautilid family Solenochildae ( Aipocerataceae ) from the Upper Mississippian of North America and equivalent ( uL Carb ) strata in Europe , first described by Foord in 1896 .
Pomacea cumingi is a species of a freshwater snail , gastropod in the family Ampullariidae .
Senilia senilis is a species of edible saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Arcidae , the ark shells .
Lomatium foeniculaceum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name desert biscuitroot .
Neolamprologus boulengeri is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is known from the Tanzanian coast in the northern part of the lake .

Pireneitega spasskyi is an araneomorph spider species found in Georgia and Azerbaijan .
Bambusa lako , known as Timor black bamboo , is a large species of bamboo originating from the island of Timor ; its black culms may reach 21 m ( 69 ft ) in height .
Gilia angelensis is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name chaparral gilia .
Monachozela neoleuca is a moth of the Heliozelidae family , and the only species in the genus Monachozela .
Allodontichthys is a genus of splitfins endemic to Mexico where it is found in the central western states of Colima and Jalisco .
Soromonichthys stearleyi is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it occurs in Soromoni Creek in Amazonas State .
Mixosaurus is an extinct genus of Middle Triassic ichthyosaur .
Hesperocallis is a genus of flowering plants that includes a single species , Hesperocallis undulata , known as the desert lily or ajo lily .
Podagrica malvae is a species of skeletonising leaf beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae , subfamily Galerucinae .
Paranthropus ( from Greek παρα , para `` beside '' ; άνθρωπος , ánthropos `` human '' ) is a genus of extinct hominins .
Melica argyrea is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Argentina , Brazil ( Rio Grande do Sul ) , and Uruguay .
Pertusaria diluta is a species of fungi within the Pertusariaceae family , first found in inland rainforests of British Columbia .
Cypripedium calceolus is a lady's - slipper orchid , and the type species of the genus Cypripedium .
Acromantis oligoneura is a species of praying mantis described by Wilhelm de Haan in 1842 .
Polygonum engelmannii , common name Engelmann 's knotweed , is a North American species of plants in the buckwheat family .
Ptilocnemus lemur is a species of feather - legged bug in the family Reduviidae native to Australia .
Lygodesmia , called skeletonplant , is a genus of North American flowering plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Fusinus novaehollandiae is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails and tulip snails .
Poria weirii is a fungus species in the genus Poria .
Jumellea exilis is a species of flowering plant in the Orchidaceae family , endemic to the island of Réunion .
Eucrossus villicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Eucrossus .
Quilmesaurus is a genus of carnivorous theropod dinosaur from the Patagonian Upper Cretaceous ( Campanian stage ) of Argentina .
Hylaeochampsidae is an extinct family of basal eusuchian crocodylomorphs thought to be closely related to the order Crocodylia .
Choristodera is an order of semi - aquatic diapsid reptiles that ranged from the Middle Jurassic , or possibly Late Triassic , to at least the early Miocene .
Chrysomphalina chrysophylla is a species of mushroom with a north temperate distribution .
The Sri Lanka Short - horned shrub frog , ( Pseudophilautus singu ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Agave geminiflora is a species of Agave endemic to the Mexican State of Nayarit .
Viola cuneata is a species of violet known by the common name wedgeleaf violet .
Cichorium is a genus of plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Stefania riveroi ( Spanish : Rana Stefania De Rivero ) is a species of frog in the family Hemiphractidae .
Neraudia melastomifolia , known as Maʻaloa in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the nettle family , Urticaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Phlox diffusa is a species of phlox known by the common name spreading phlox .
Aedes sollicitans , the eastern saltmarsh mosquito ( also known as Ochlerotatus sollicitans ) , is a species of mosquito native to the eastern seaboard of the United States and Canada as well as the entire Gulf coast and is also present in the Bahamas and Greater Antilles .
Microrhodopina flavescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Microrhodopina .
Proscopiidae is a family of Neotropical stick grasshoppers or jumping sticks .
Ilex arnhemensis is the only species of Ilex ( Holly ) native to Australia .
Michel Dens ( 22 June 1911 , Roubaix -- 19 December 2000 , Paris ) was a French baritone , particularly associated with the French repertory , both opera and operetta .
Durward Lely ( 2 September 1852 -- 29 February 1944 ) was a Scottish opera singer and actor primarily known as the creator of five tenor roles in Gilbert and Sullivan 's comic operas , including Nanki - Poo in The Mikado .
